<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Vietnam-Military </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Vietnam launches military knowledge course for top civilians
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HANOI, Vietnam (AP) _ Vietnam has launched a military classroom
course for senior civilian officials to ensure they can respond to
a crisis quickly, a newspaper reported Tuesday.
	   The communist party newspaper Nhan Dan said that 48 senior
provincial party and government officials took part in the first
course starting Monday at the Military Academy.
	   The participants will learn Vietnamese military history, the
party's position on military and security affairs, the building of
the armed forces, provincial defense systems and a combination of
military and economic tasks.
	   Party General Secretary Le Kha Phieu said officials should have
knowledge not only about social and economic affairs, but also
military and security issues.
	   Phieu said maintaining political stability is essential for
Vietnam and the country is ready to spoil any attempt to violate
its sovereignty or sabotage the communist regime. 	   
</TEXT>
