<SLUG> BC-Iran-Floods, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Floods kill 16 in northwestern Iran
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: RECATS to identify the news agency in the lead.

<TEXT>
	   TEHRAN, Iran (AP) _ Floods caused by heavy rains have killed at
least 16 people in northwestern Iran over the past month, the
official Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
	   The floods, which hit some 10 towns in the East Azerbaijan
province, also damaged homes and farmlands, the agency said late
Monday. It gave no other details.
	   In April, 81 people were killed by floods in the southwestern
provinces of Khuzestan and Charmahal-va-Bakhtiyari.
