<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Myanmar-Drugs </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Myanmar police seize 1 million amphetamine pills, arrest three
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   YANGON, Myanmar (AP) _ Police have arrested three people and
seized more than 1 million amphetamine tablets that were apparently
being smuggled to Thailand, official newspapers reported Tuesday.
	   Amphetamine production has soared in recent years in the
notorious Golden Triangle region where the borders of Myanmar, Laos
and Thailand converge. The area has long been one of the world's
principal sources of opium and its derivative, heroin.
	   Police reportedly stopped a car carrying the tablets in secret
compartments at a checkpoint near the northeastern town of
Kengtung. The car was heading for Tachilek, on the Thai border.
	   The three men in the car were being detained pending trial, the
newspapers said. Drug trafficking carries the death penalty. 	   
</TEXT>
