<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-China-Dissidents, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
23 dissidents urge Clinton, Jiang to discuss human rights
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: CORRECTS number who signed letter to 23 sted 22; ADDS comment
from copy of letter; CHANGES attribution throughout; no pickup. &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   BEIJING (AP) _ Twenty-three Chinese dissidents sent an open
letter Tuesday to presidents Jiang Zemin and Bill Clinton urging
them to make human rights an important topic at the upcoming
China-U.S. summit.
	   The democracy activists wrote that China's ruling Communist
Party has disregarded the meaning of human rights and rudely
treated appeals for better rights protection since coming to power
in 1949.
	   Observance of human rights has deteriorated further since March,
the letter said, citing cases of dissidents around the country who
recently have been detained or sent to labor camps without trial.
	   The two presidents, who will meet in Beijing in late June,
should discuss how China can enforce the protection of basic rights
called for in two U.N. treaties, the letter said.
	   China signed the International Covenant on Economic, Social and
Cultural Rights, but has not yet ratified it. It has announced it
plans to sign the International Covenant on Civil and Political
Rights.
	   ``Only when the rights of all people are respected and the
dignity of all people is protected can a country have booming
development and the whole world have peace and prosperity,'' the
letter said.
	   The activists also asked the presidents to discuss efforts by Xu
Wenli and Qin Yongmin to establish a human rights monitoring group
in China. Authorities have confiscated office equipment and have
refused to allow the group to register as a legal entity, the
letter said.
	   It added that police are preventing Xu from leaving his home.
	   Xu and Qin, longtime activists, were among the 23 who signed the
letter.
</TEXT>
(PROFILE
(WS SL:BC-China-Dissidents, 1st Ld-Writethru; CT:i; 
(REG:EURO;)
(REG:BRIT;)
(REG:SCAN;)
(REG:MEST;)
(REG:AFRI;)
(REG:INDI;)
(REG:ENGL;)
(LANG:ENGLISH;))
