<HEADLINE>
Report: Newspaper editor killed
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ The body of a newspaper editor was found in the
southern republic of Kalmykia after she went to a meeting with
people who said they had important documents, the ITAR-Tass news
agency reported Tuesday.
	   Citing local police, the report said Larisa Yudina disappeared
Sunday after leaving her home in Elista, capital of the Kalmyk
Republic in south Russia.
	   Her body, bearing signs of a violent attack, was found in a pond
in Elista, the report said. Police declined to confirm or deny
reports that Yudina had been stabbed, it said.
	   Yudina was also co-chairman of the local branch of Yabloko, the
country's main liberal political party.
