<SLUG> BC-Germany-Unemployment </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
German unemployment rate drops for May
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   NUREMBERG, Germany (AP) _ Germany's unemployment crisis eased in
May, with 223,400 more people working than in the previous month,
the Federal Labor Office said Tuesday.
	   A total 4.2 million people remained jobless _ or 10.9 percent of
the work force compared to 11.1 percent in April. It was the first
time since 1996 that the rate has sunk below 11 percent.
	   Compared to May 1997, 58,300 more people had jobs, making it the
first time in almost three years that unemployment has improved on
the year.
	   Unemployment is the key issue in national elections Sept. 27,
and thousands of people have been protesting joblessness in recent
months.
	   Last week, Chancellor Helmut Kohl revealed the unemployment
figures early, saying the main goal of his political platform was
``to give people who want to work the chance to work.''
	   (aet/cb) 	   
</TEXT>
