<SLUG> BC--Bosnia-Arrest </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Police round up smugglers
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSTAR, Bosnia-Herzegovina (AP) _ Police of the Muslim-Croat
federation have arrested three persons, smashing up what they say
was a ring of drug and car smugglers operating between the two
Bosnian substates and Italy, a police statement said Tuesday.
	   On June 4, federal police stopped a Mercedes-Benz car with
Croatian license plates near the southern town of Stolac. More than
four kilograms (nearly 9 pounds) of heroin were confiscated and
three people in the car, all residents of Zagreb, the Croat
capital, were arrested, it said.
	   Federal police cooperated with Croatian police and Interpol to
track down and destroy the ring of smugglers, the statement said,
adding the action was continuing.
	   With border porous and officials corrupt, Bosnia frequently has
been a conduit used by international smugglers during and after the
1992-95 war for smuggling guns, drugs and stolen cars.
	   (sl/rp) 	   
