<HEADLINE>
China evacuates nationals, calls on Ethiopia, Eritrea to talk
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BEIJING (AP) _ As Ethiopia attacked Eritrea in a war over
disputed territory Tuesday, China said it evacuated Chinese
citizens from the Horn of Africa nations.
	   Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao said some embassy staff
and representatives of Chinese businesses were evacuated to ensure
their safety.
	   He did not say how many people departed and by what means but he
added that China's embassies were still open.
	   Noting China's ``friendly'' relations with both countries, Zhu
said, ``We sincerely hope the dispute can be resolved peacefully
through negotiations.''
	   Once a close ally of Ethiopia's longtime military ruler Mengistu
Haile Mariam, China moved to maintain the ties after he was ousted
in 1991 and swiftly opened relations with Eritrea when it declared
independence from Ethiopia in 1992.
