<HEADLINE>
Officials: more than dlrs 25 billion smuggled out of Russia
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ More than dlrs 25 billion have been smuggled out
of Russia illegally since the Soviet collapse, security officials
said Tuesday.
	   Most of the money has gone to bank accounts in Switzerland,
Cyprus, Britain and Israel, the Interfax news agency reported,
citing Russian security services that are investigating capital
flight.
	   Between dlrs 25 billion and dlrs 27 billion have been smuggled
by companies and individuals, usually to evade taxes, Interfax
reported.
	   Investigators said they have leads on dlrs 5 billion of the
money and are trying to track it down, it said.
	   (ad/ren)
</TEXT>
