<SLUG> BC-Ukraine-Treasure </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Ukrainian villager faces trial for failing to report treasure
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) - A Ukrainian villager is facing trial for
finding a treasure of ancient coins and failing to report it to the
authorities, a newspaper reported Tuesday.
	   Ukrainian law says buried treasure belongs to the state, and
anyone finding it can only hope to receive 25 percent of the value
as estimated by the authorities.
	   But the villager in the eastern settlement of Krivoposevki
decided that he had other uses for a jug filled with 18th century
silver coins from the reign of Russian Empress Catherine the Great,
the daily Dyen said.
	   The villager, whose name was not released, found the 29 silver
rubles last month and sold them for 10 hryvna (dlrs 5) each to
other villagers. However, police soon found the man and he is
facing a possible fine.
	   (sms/ren)
</TEXT>
