<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-China-Police Fired </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Chinese province dismisses 133 police for incompetence
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BEIJING (AP) _ Provincial authorities in southwestern Guizhou
province have dismissed 133 police officials for incompetence,
corruption and other misdeeds, the state-run Xinhua News Agency
reported Tuesday.
	   Among those fired by the end of May was a police officer who had
taken 3,000 yuan (dlrs 363) in bribes and cigarettes. He was
sentenced to two years in prison, the report said.
	   It said 92 other police who had violeted regulations would also
be dismissed.
	   Meanwhile, the Ministry of Public Security announced it would
organize expert teams to advise some 150,000 police involved in
criminal investigations on how to handle cases according to the
newly revised Criminal Law.
	   The amended law is intended to better protect the rights of
those accused of crimes by police and during the trial process.
Chinese officials acknowledge, however, that compliance with the
law is inconsistent.
	   The training is intended to improve the effectiveness of police
in cracking cases and in handling cases according to the law, the
newspaper China Daily reported. 	   
</TEXT>
