<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-China-Italy </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Italian, Chinese presidents meet in Beijing
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; AP Photos 101-104

<TEXT>
	   BEIJING (AP) _ China wants to continue developing good relations
with Italy, Chinese President Jiang Zemin said Tuesday in talks
with visiting Italian President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro.
	   Although the two countries have different problems, social
systems and cultural traditions, they have no major conflicts of
interest, Jiang said according to the state-run Xinhua News Agency.
	   ``We are moving toward a multi-polarized world, and Asia and
Europe are trying to establish a new partnership. So improved
Sino-Italian cooperation not only serves the two nations, it also
is in the interest of world peace, stability and development,''
Jiang said.
	   Many Italian companies have invested in China, and there is
great potential for further economic ties and trade between the two
countries, Jiang said.
	   Scalfaro invited Jiang to visit Italy, and Jiang accepted,
Xinhua said.
	   The two presidents attended a signing ceremony for a joint
statement and a cooperation agreement on science and technology.
	   Scalfaro arrived in Beijing Monday on a six-day state visit. 	   
</TEXT>
