<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Poland-Shooting </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Five dead, six injured in shooting
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   WARSAW, Poland (AP) _ A 60-year-old man who flew into a rage
during a family gathering shot and killed his wife, daughter and
two neighbors before killing himself, police in the southwestern
city of Opole said Tuesday.
	   Five people, including the man's 18-year-old grandson, were in
critical condition.
	   Investigators were trying to determine a motive.
	   They said that the shooter, identified as Zbigniew Wolczuk,
started firing a Polish-made TT revolver out the window of his home
Monday evening, hitting five neighbors, then turned the gun on
family members inside.
	   Before shooting himself, the man killed also his dog.
	   Police said that the man was a hunter, and had a collection of
guns and rifles, including the TT revolver once commonly used by
police.
