<HEADLINE>
Russian president and German chancellor hopeful meet
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; With BC-Germany-Russia &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   BONN, Germany (AP) _ Russian President Boris Yeltsin pledged
cooperation Tuesday with the man who hopes to unseat Yeltsin's
longtime friend and ally, Chancellor Helmut Kohl, in Germany's
September elections.
	   Lower Saxony governor Gerhard Schroeder met for 40 minutes with
the Russian president before Yeltsin headed into talks with Kohl
focusing on European security and Russia's recent financial crisis.
	   Schroeder told reporters Yeltsin emphasized that good
German-Russian relations must continue no matter who is elected to
lead Germany. Schroeder called for strengthening ties by expanding
contacts between entrepreneurs, cultural institutions and the two
nations' regions.
	   Schroeder has been leading Kohl in the polls ahead of the Sept.
27 vote. Kohl is seeking an unprecedented fifth term.
