<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Chelsea-Ferrer </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Chelsea signs Spanish defender
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Chelsea manager Gianluca Vialli continued his
off-season international recruitment drive, signing Spanish right
back Albert Ferrer for five years in a reported 2.2 million pound
(dlrs 3.6 million) deal.
	   The European Cup Winners Cup champions lured the Spanish
international from Barcelona five days before he kicks off his
World Cup campaign for Spain against Nigeria in Nantes.
	   Chelsea adds Ferrer to a list of recent international signings,
including a club record 5.4 million pound (dlrs 8.8 million) deal
with Italian Pierluigi Casiraghi two weeks ago.
	   Ferrer, who turned 28 Saturday, has a wealth of international
experience. He has 35 caps for Spain, the 1992 Olympic gold medal,
as well as five Spanish League championship medals, the European
Cup and two Cup Winner's Cups.
	   Ferrer and Chelsea concluded negotiations at the Spanish World
Cup training base in Chantilly on Monday night.
	   Ferrer, who has made 330 league and cup appearances for
Barcelona since 1990, said was he very happy to join the Blues.
	   ``I've played in the Champions League but I think this will be a
new experience for me and I think that experience will be very
successful,'' he said.
	   (jp) 	   
