<HEADLINE>
Police free bank employees after robbery attempt
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with bank employees freed, more details

<TEXT>
	   BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) _ Police freed two bank employees trapped
in their workplace during a hold-up Tuesday in Brussels, but two
suspected robbers appeared to have escaped.
	   Fearing the employees were being held hostage, members of a
police SWAT team surrounded the bank in the Molenbeek district of
the Belgium capital shortly after robbery started at 9.0 a.m.
(0700). When police entered the building two hours later they found
the two women, but not the assailants.
	   A third suspected member of the gang was caught as he tried to
flee shortly after the start of the attempted robbery. Police were
searching neighboring houses in an attempt to find the others.
	   It was unclear if the employees had been held hostage or if they
had hidden from the robbers.
