<HEADLINE>
Brazil's Goncalves ready to replace injured Aldair
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LESIGNY, France (AP) _ Brazilian coach Mario Zagallo has
penciled in Goncalves to start in the World Cup opener if injured
fullback Aldair isn't fit.
	   Zagallo said he would withhold a final decision until team
doctor Lidio Toledo examines Aldair after practice Tuesday at Saint
Denis stadium, where Brazil and Scotland meet on Wednesday.
	   Aldair, a starter on Brazil's 1994 Cup champions, and his
replacement, Andre Cruz, reported sore leg muscles and didn't train
with the team on Monday.
