<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Burundi-Rebels </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Army kills 13 rebels in clash, one soldier dies
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BUJUMBURA, Burundi (AP) _ The army killed 13 rebels in a clash
in southern Burundi in which one government soldier died, army
spokesman Lt. Col. Isaie Nibizi said Tuesday.
	   The fighting occurred June 6 at Kiderege in Makamba province,
123 kilometers (75 miles) south of Bujumbura.
	   ``We want to end the rebellion in this country, we want to
neutralize it,'' Nibizi said.
	   The Tutsi-dominated army and the Hutu rebels have been battling
since late 1993 after Tutsi paratroopers assassinated Burundi's
first democratically election president, Hutu Melchoir Ndadaye.
	   At least 200,000 people, most of them civilians, have been
killed in the fighting.
	   On Monday, another round of talks on peace in Burundi is
scheduled to begin in the northern Tanzanian town of Arusha under
the mediation for former President Julius Nyerere.
	   President Pierre Buyoya, who overthrew a coalition Hutu-Tutsi
government in July 1996, will take part in the talks for the first
time.
	   (cn/sl)
	   Burundipeace talks is scheduled to open i
