<SLUG> BC-Germany-VW-Renault </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Report: Volkswagen interested in merger with Renault
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HAMBURG, Germany (AP) _ Fresh from its purchase of British
luxury automaker Rolls-Royce, Volkswagen reportedly is looking to
buy something French: Renault.
	   Stern magazine reported Tuesday that VW, Europe's biggest
carmaker, is interested in a merger with Renault mainly for its
truck division. Renault is the third biggest manufacturer of
commercial vehicles in the world.
	   VW Chairman Ferdinand Piech has often said he would like to add
a truck division to VW _ either through an acquisition or through
internal development.
	   VW spokesman Kurt Rippholz called the Stern report ``pure
speculation'' and declined to comment further.
	   The magazine also said VW plans for luxury cars did not end with
its recent acquisition of Rolls-Royce.
	   According to Stern, VW plans to build a Horch luxury model, with
an 18-cylinder motor, in Dresden.
	   Last month VW's high-end unit, Audi AG, confirmed it was
considering a joint project with Lamborghini, but declined to
comment on a Stern report that it might buy the Italian sportscar
maker.
 &UR; (pfg-cb)
</TEXT>
