<SLUG> BC-Netherlands-Prince-Prostate Surgery </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Dutch Prince operated for `malignant condition' in prostate
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   THE HAGUE, Netherlands (AP) _ Prince Claus, the husband of Dutch
Queen Beatrix, underwent emergency surgery Tuesday to remove his
prostate gland after doctors discovered what the Royal House
described as ``a malignant condition.''
	   A spokesman speaking on customary condition of anonymity said he
could not be more specific about the condition.
	   German-born Claus, 71, underwent surgery at the Allgemeines
Krankenhaus Barmbek in Hamburg, Germany early Tuesday morning. The
surgery was a success, the Royal House announced in a press
statement.
	   German surgeon Ronald Tauber performed the operation. Claus, who
suffers from Parkinson's disease, chose the surgeon himself. No
further details of the surgery were released.
	   The condition was discovered last week during a checkup in
Hamburg. Surgeons recommended surgery as soon as possible.
	   Claus was expected to spend ``some time'' in hospital recovering
from the surgery, the Royal House statement said.
	   A German aristocrat by birth, Claus married then Princess
Beatrix March 10, 1966 in Amsterdam. The princess' marriage to a
German sparked riots in the Dutch capital where memories of the
brutal World War II occupation of the Netherlands were still fresh.
	   (mc) 	   
</TEXT>
