<HEADLINE>
Sir Derek Jacobi gets German Shakespeare prize
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HAMBURG, Germany (AP) _ British actor Sir Derek Jacobi was named
the winner of this year's Hamburg Shakespeare Prize on Tuesday by
the Alfred Toepfer Foundation.
	   The 59-year-old actor will receive the award, endowed with
40,000 marks (dlrs 23,000), June 18 at the Hamburg city hall. The
foundation called him one of Britain's most important actors,
especially praising his portrayals of Hamlet, Richard II and
Richard III.
	   Past recipients include authors Graham Greene and Doris Lessing
and playwright Harold Pinter.
