 &UR; BASKETBALL:
	   CHICAGO _ Dennis Rodman, basketball's poster boy for bad
behavior, is fined dlrs 10,000 by the NBA for missing practice and
the mandatory National Basketball Association Finals media session
by attending a professional wrestling match.
	   Slug Sports-Basketball-NBA Finals-Bulls. Has moved.
	   By Nancy Armour
 &UR; GOLF:
	   CINCINNATI _ Casey Martin overcomes a balky cart and a double
bogey on the 36th hole before qualifying for the U.S. Open in a
two-hole playoff. Martin, who won a court order to ride a cart
because of a circulation problem with his right leg, takes a while
to adjust to a new one-person cart brought in for the event.
	   Slug Sports-Golf-Martin-US Open. Has moved.
	   By Joe Kay
 &UR; RUGBY:
	   SYDNEY, Australia _ Scotland loses its first match on the
Australian leg of its southern rugby tour, falling 39-34 to the
Australian Barbarians at Penrith.
	   Slug Sports-RugbyU-Australian Barbarians-Scotland. Has moved.
	   AUCKLAND, New Zealand _ Star winger Jonah Lomu must dominate
struggling England on Saturday to hang onto his All Blacks jersey
for the June 20 rugby test.
	   Slug Sports-RugbyU-New Zealand-Team. Has moved.
 &UR; BASEBALL:
	   NEW YORK _ Theories abound as to why Hideo Nomo is no longer the
pitcher that mystified National League hitters three years ago. He
tips his pitches, goes one. Hitters have figured out his quirky
delivery is another. Nomo, who makes his first start for the New
York Mets, has a theory of his own. ``Simply put,'' he says, ``I've
been getting hit.''
	   Slug Sports-Baseball-Mets-Nomo. Has moved.
	   By Tom Withers
