<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Chelsea-Ferrer, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Chelsea signs Spanish defender
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: updates with Ferrer quotes

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Chelsea manager Gianluca Vialli continued his
off-season international recruitment drive, signing Spanish right
back Albert Ferrer for five years in a reported 2.2 million pound
(dlrs 3.6 million) deal.
	   The European Cup Winners Cup champions lured the Spanish
international from Barcelona five days before he kicks off his
World Cup campaign for Spain against Nigeria in Nantes.
	   ``I'm sad to be leaving Barcelona,'' Ferrer said Tuesday at the
Spanish World Cup team base in Chantilly, north of Paris. ``I
didn't want to leave but I'm happy to be joining another great
European club.''
	   Chelsea adds Ferrer to a list of recent international signings,
including a club record 5.4 million pound (dlrs 8.8 million) deal
with Italian Pierluigi Casiraghi two weeks ago.
	   Ferrer, who turned 28 Saturday, has a wealth of international
experience. He has 35 caps for Spain, the 1992 Olympic gold medal,
as well as five Spanish League championship medals, the European
Cup and two Cup Winner's Cups.
	   Ferrer, known as ``Chapi'' in Spain, has made 330 league and cup
appearances for Barcelona since 1990. He is a terrier-like defender
and a regular Spanish team starter.
	   ``I hope to debut for Chelsea on August 28 in the Supercup game
against Real Madrid,'' he said. ``I will go all out to help win
that game as it is important to begin a new period by winning.''
	   Ferrer declined to comment on Barcelona coach Louis Van Gaal's
decision to let him go, saying ``that's his opinion.''
	   ``But I hope to demonstrate with Chelsea that I am still able to
play at top level soccer,'' he said.
</TEXT>
