world's nuclear powers to take immediate steps to dispose of their
arsenals within a few years. IRELAND-NUCLEAR.
	   MINSK, Belarus _ The U.S. ambassador and other envoys were
refusing Tuesday to budge after the Belarusian government said they
had to leave their residences to allow repairs and renovations.
BELARUS-US.
	   MOSCOW _ The head of the government's statistics service was
arrested Tuesday on charges of helping tax dodgers and selling
confidential data. Investigators said they found over dlrs 1
million in cash at his apartment. RUSSIA-ARREST.
	   VATICAN CITY _ Pope John Paul II prodded Cuba's government
Tuesday to make greater openings and urged his bishops to keep up
the momentum begun by his visit to the communist island.
VATICAN-CUBA.
