<HEADLINE>
Jamaat asks people to foil govt conspiracy against CHT, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
Jamaat asks people to foil govt conspiracy against CHT, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Jamaat-e-Islami assistant secretary general, Mohammad
Quamaruzzaman, yesterday urged the people to foil the government
``conspiracy'' against the Chittagong Hill Tracts by participating
in the long march.
	   He was speaking as the chief guest at a rally organised by the
party's city unit prior to a procession in support of the long
march. Jamaat city ameer ATM Azharul Islam presided. Jamaat city
unit leaders Dr. Syed Abdullah Md Taher and Saiful Alam Khan also
spoke.
	   Quamaruzzaman warned the government against using police force
to harass people during the long march. He said the government
would be held responsible for the occurrence of any untoward
incident during the long march.
	   Jamaat brought out processions and organised street corner
meetings in different parts of the city yesterday in support of the
long march.
	   Jatiya Party co-chairman and former prime minister Kazi Zafar
Ahmed yesterday said that if any obstacle was created against the
long march, then a programme for ousting the government would be
announced.
	   He was speaking at a meeting of the long march preparatory
committee of his party at its temporary office at Banani.
	   JP secretary general Shamim Al Mamun, presidium member Mainuddin
Bhuiyan and Ismail Hossain Bengal also spoke.
	   
</TEXT>
