<HEADLINE>
BCL rally protests long march, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
BCL rally protests long march, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   The ruling party-backed Bangladesh Chhatra League (BCL)
yesterday brought out a peace procession in the city centring
today's long march to Khagrachhari by the main opposition BNP and
its allies.
	   The BCL (S-P) procession paraded the city's main thoroughfares.
Processionists carried white flags, and photographs of Prime
Minister Sheikh Hasina. It chanted slogans against the long march
after gathering at Bot Tola of Dhaka University at around noon.
	   The BCL (S-P) members held a rally on the campus prior to the
procession protesting what they called the BNP's plan to create
anarchy in the name of long march.
	   Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina had established peace in Chittagong
Hill Tracts through the signing of the historic CHT peace accord,
said the BCL (S-P) leaders.
	   They also called upon their members to remain alert against any
conspiracy to foil the peaceful atmosphere in the CHT.
	   Presided over by BCL (S-P) President Enamul Haq Shamim, the
rally was addressed, among others, by General Secretary Ishaq Ali
Khan Panna, Ajoykor Khokon, Bahadur Bepary, Abdul Oadud Khokon and
Rafiqul Islam Kotwal.
	   
</TEXT>
