<HEADLINE>
Bomb attack on BNP, Jamaat rallies in Barisal, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
Bomb attack on BNP, Jamaat rallies in Barisal, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Two rallies organised separate by the BNP and the Jamaat in
support of the long march to the CHT could not be held here this
afternoon following bomb attacks allegedly by the Bangladesh
Chhatra League, the student wing of the ruling party.
	   A group of armed youths allegedly belonging to the BCL also
attacked two launches at the Barisal launch terminal. The launches
were scheduled to carry the long marchers to Dhaka.
	   The youths were reportedly under heavy protection of a
contingent of police during the incident.
	   The activists of the BCL who brought out a ``peace procession''
at about 4 pm launched a bomb attack on BNP activists who gathered
in front of the BNP office to hold a pre-long march rally. The BCL
activists later attacked the BNP and the Juba Dal offices. They
ransacked the two offices and threw chairs, tables and other
materials on the road.
	   The BCL activists also hurled bombs at ``Aviruchi'' cinema owned
by a local BNP leader.
	   Later BCL activists went to the launch terminal where two
launches - ``Parabat'' and ``Tibraj-2'' were kept ready to take the
long marchers to Dhaka. They allegedly beat up the long marchers on
board the launches and threw away their belongings. Seven BNP
activists were injured and two Jamaat activists were thrown into
the Kirtonkhola river.
	   A rally of the Jamaat which was schedule to be held at
Girjamahalla was also foiled by the BCL activists.
	   
</TEXT>
