<SLUG> MAKITA-WANTS-TO-SET sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Makita wants to set up industrial unit in Bangladesh, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
Makita wants to set up industrial unit in Bangladesh, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Makita Corporation, a renowned industrial power tools
manufacturer in Japan, on Monday launched its marketing in
Bangladesh.
	   Superior Builders and Engineers Ltd, Bangladesh is the sole
distributor of Makita products in the country.
	   Some 37 kinds of portable industrial power tools which are being
introduced in Bangladesh include hammer drill, scraper screwdriver,
auto-feed screwdriver, wrench dise sander, grinder, saw,
planer-jointer, shear and blower.
	   R Maksud Khan, President of Dhaka Chamber of Commerce and
Industry (DCCI), opened the launching of Makita product at a
function held at a city hotel.
	   Attended by suppliers and dealers, the function was addressed by
Satoru Watanabe, Managing Director of Makita Corporation, Japan,
Kazuya Nakamura, and Engr Manzarul Ahsan MP, Chairman of Superior
Builders and Engineers, Bangladesh.
	   Appreciating marketing of Makita power tools, R Maksud said that
it would help industrial as well as domestic activities in the
country.
	   He expressed the hope that Superior Builders and Engineers would
be able to manufanture power tools in the country with the
assistance of Makita in near future.
	   Manzarul Ahsan said his company had already established an
after-sales and backup centre at Nowabpur road in the city to
provide service to the users.
	   He said users would get service including replacement of spare
parts from the engineers and technicians trained from the Makita
workshop in Singapore.
	   Makita products would be popular in the country very soon for
its quality and reasonable price, he hoped.
	   Headquatered in Anjo, near Nagoya, Makita designs manufacturers
and markets at least 900 types of power tools. Makita also offers
stationary wood-dorking machines, pneumatic tools, gardening tools
and indoor household products.
	   APB adds: A leading Japanese power tools company evinced
interest in setting up an industrial unit in Bangladesh for
manufacturing their products here.
	   ``We are actually considering setting up a manufacturing unit in
South Asia but we well give Bangladesh priority if our products go
well here,'' said Kazuya Nakamura, Managing Director of Makita
Singapore Ltd.
	   Talking to APB, Nakamura said: ``It would take time to set up a
unit as you know the economic situation in South Asia is not
good.''
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 THE INDEPENDENT all rights reserved as
distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
