<HEADLINE>
CSE index dips 9 pts, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
CSE index dips 9 pts, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   The price index at the Chittagong Stock Exchange Monday further
dipped shedding 9.09 points or 2.9 per cent with most of the isues
registering decling.
	   The CSE All Securities Price Index stood at 302.99 on the day
from 312.05 points on Sunday.
	   A total of 202,665 shares worth Tk. 10.91 million were traded on
the CSE floor against 304,615 shares valued at Tk. 13.94 million on
the previous day.
	   The losers maintained a clear domination over the gainers on the
day. Out of 38 traded issues three gained and 35 tumbled.
	   Market capitalisation stood at Tk. 51.37 billion equivalent to
USS 1.10 billion, from Tk. 52.88 billion on Sunday.
	   
