<HEADLINE>
Film shown in schools to foster patriotism, HONGKONG STANDARD
</HEADLINE>
Film shown in schools to foster patriotism, HONGKONG STANDARD &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   HONGKONG STANDARD
   HONG KONG
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   THE national anthem was played and the flag raised in front of
hundreds of students yesterday _ on screens showing education
television programs.
	   The 15-minute film _ Under Our National Flag _ was aired for the
first time during civic education lessons at primary schools to
boost students' sense of patriotism.
	   It shows the flag raising ceremony with the national anthem
being played.
	   The screening is part of the Education Department's efforts ``to
promote civic education and instil a sense of identity with the
motherland'', a department spokesman said. ``It will also enhance a
proper understanding and respect among students for the national
and regional flags, emblems and national anthem.'' Schools have
been encouraged to fly the national flag and to teach their
students to sing the anthem on days such as the anniversary of the
handover and national day.
	   
