	   KUALA LUMPUR, Mon. - In a kind gesture that is hoped to motivate
others to do likewise, 25 Public Service Department's pension
division staff donated a portion of their monetary award to the
National Special Fund.
	   The staff, who had earlier received their bonus at an excellent
service award ceremony, collected the money and handed a RM1,240
cheque to PSD director-general Tan Sri Dr Mazlan Ahmad.
	   Pension division assistant director Shamsuddin Yunus said
although the contribution to the fund was small, it was done with
sincerity which could set a good example.
	   ``I don't know of any other government staff who had done
this,'' he said at his office today.
	   He said the contribution was also a reflection of the PSD
staff's patriotism apart from their gratitude for having been given
the excellent service award.
	   The National Special Fund was set up in March 6 to collect
donations and valuables to boost national reserves and help
economic recovery.
	   
