<HEADLINE>
Colin McRae wins Acropolis Rally
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ATHENS, Greece (AP) _ Coming from behind, British driver Colin
McRae, driving a Subarau Impreza, won the Acropolis Rally Tuesday.
	   McRae beat France's Didier Auriol by 20 seconds in the last
stage, after Auriol, in his Toyota Corolla, had led the second day
of the three-day rally.
	   McRae crossed the finish line in four hours, 26 minutes and 31
seconds, against Auriol's 4:26.51.
