<HEADLINE>
Foot bridge to be closed from tomorrow, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Foot bridge to be closed from tomorrow, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   BUTTERWORTH, Mon. - The wooden foot bridge linking the Sultan
Abdul Halim ferry terminal with the Keretapi Tanah Melayu Bhd
railway station here will be closed indefinitely from noon on
Wednesday.
	   A KTM Rail Sdn Bhd spokesman said the closure was necessary to
facilitate the construction of the proposed 3.1km railway tracks
linking the station to the North Butterworth Container Terminal.
	   He advised ferry users and those from the Penang Port Commission
complex intending to reach the railway station to use alternative
routes to reach their destination.
	   ``Only foot passengers intending to reach the station or from
the station to proceed to the complex will be affected by the
closure. The foot bridge linking the Penang Port Commission complex
to the ferry terminal will not be closed.''
	   It is estimated that 11,000 people use the foot bridges daily.
	   Work on the railway track, costing RM235 million, is expected to
be completed by the end of next year.
	   
</TEXT>
