<HEADLINE>
Fighters beat BlueWave 13-4
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TOKYO (AP) _ The Pacific League's front-running Nippon Ham
Fighters rapped out 16 hits, including a grand slam home run by
Jerry Brooks, trouncing the Orix BlueWave 13-4 at Tokyo Dome on
Tuesday.
	   Brooks, formerly with the Florida Marlins, has 11 homers.
	   The Fighters are one game ahead of the second-place Fukuoka
Daiei Hawks, who beat the Seibu Lions 9-3 at Yamagata.
	   The Hawks' Hiroki Kokubo hit a two-run home run, his first homer
of the season, in the fifth inning.
	   The Lions' Domingo Martinez, formerly with the Triple-A
Rochester, hit a home run, his 12th homer of the season, in the
eighth inning.
	   At Chiba, Joe Crawford hurled a four-hitter over seven innings
for his fourth victory against four defeats as the Chiba Lotte
Marines edged the Kintetsu Buffaloes 3-2.
	   The Marines scored three runs on two home runs _ a home run by
Iwao Oomura in the fourth and a two-run home run by Kiyoshi
Hatsushiba in the sixth. Oomura has one homer and Hatsushiba 11
homers this season.
	   In the Central League, Takanori Suzuki hit a one-run single and
Norihiro Komada also drove in another run with an infield hit in
the two-run eighth as the Yokohama BayStars beat the Yakult
Swallows 2-0 at Tokyo's Jingu Stadium.
	   Two other scheduled games were rained out.
 &UR; (sk) 	   
