<HEADLINE>
Council pledges quick response, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Council pledges quick response, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KOTA KINABALU, Mon. - The Kota Kinabalu Municipal Council will
try to respond to Press inquiries the soonest possible and as
``transparently'' as can be.
	   At a luncheon with reporters today, council president Datuk
Dayang Adeline Leong, said that as a responsible local authority
the KKMC administration realised the need to get public opinion.
	   The media would be among those in the best position to assist.
	   ``In many instances, the media can influence its readers,
viewers and listeners, and can help to clarify matters, or vice
versa.
	   ``I am proud and happy to say that almost all reporters have
been very reasonable in carrying out their tasks.''
	   Leong said KKMC would also continue efforts to improve what it
had achieved over the years such as the implementation of the MS
ISO9002 quality system, which was a way towards Total Quality
improvement.
	   Sabah Journalists' Association president Joniston Bangkuai was
also present.
	   
</TEXT>
