<HEADLINE>
Naziur sues editor, publisher of Muktakantha, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
Naziur sues editor, publisher of Muktakantha, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Jatiya Party secretary general Naziur Rahman Monzur yesterday
filed a defamation suit claiming damages of Tk 5 crore against the
editor and the publisher of the daily Muktakantha and Iffat Obayed,
widow of Awami League leader Obaidul Haque Babul, who was killed by
some miscreants on October 10, 1996.
	   Monzur alleged that the Muktakantha editor, KG Mostafa, and its
publisher, Iqbal Ahmed, had defamed him by publishing his
photograph with an alleged killer of Babul in their May 28 issue
while Iffat Obayed, the widow of Babul, defamed him in her
interview with the dailies Manobjamin on March 2 and Muktakantha on
May 31 saying the mastermind behind the killing of Babul was Naziur
Rahman Monzur.
	   The plaintiff prayed for a decree of Tk 5 crore in favour of him
against the defendants, costs of the suit, and any other relief or
reliefs he was entitled to get under law and equity.
	   The case, no 12, was filed in the court of Fourth Sub-judge of
Dhaka.
	   
