<HEADLINE>
Burst pipe disrupts water supply, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Burst pipe disrupts water supply, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   PENANG, Mon. - A leak in an underground pipe in Jalan Mesjid
Negeri about 3am yesterday disrupted water supply for 17 hours to
about 1,500 homes in the Island Glades and Island Park areas.
	   Penang Water Authority technician Mohd Sheriff Mahmud, who led a
10-man repair team, said supply was restored by 7pm.
	   Repair work caused a massive traffic jam in the evening from the
junction of Jalan Batu Lanchang and Jalan Mesjid Negeri to Jalan
Udini and Jalan Sultan Azlan Shah.
	   Jalan Mesjid Negeri had to be closed as the pipe is located in
the middle of it.
	   He said a motorcyclist lost control and fell into the flooded
worksite pit. However, he was not injured.
	   Mohd Sheriff regretted that many motorists shouted derogatory
words and hooted unnecessarily despite cones being placed to
demarcate the work zone.
	   A resident, C. Selvashekar, 42, said he had to get water from
Jelutong.
	   Another resident, R. Daniel, 50, was satisfied with the PWA's
repair work.
	   
