WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   In a span of two days, two young sons of a millionaire of the
city's South Mugdapara area died in 'mysterious circumstances'.
	   Tarun and Bipu, in their twenties, sons of Dr. Yusuf Ali, a
physician and a resident of 3/Ka South Mugdapara under Sabujbag
thana, died on Friday night and Monday morning.
	   Dr. Yusuf Ali is a respected man in the area, the people said
and added that the two sons reportedly used to inclined to drink
alcohol.
	   Family sources suspected that Tarun might have died of
poisoning, after taking alcohol. The second son Bipu, who died in
the early hours of Monday in the Dhaka Medical College Hospital
(DMCH), had reportedly taken phensidyl on Sunday night.
	   Sabujbag police said they did not receive any report about the
death.
	   It is said that three other children of Dr. Yusuf, including a
son and two daughters were killed in a road accident in 1988.
	   The parents now have a lone daughter living in Saudi Arabia.
	   
