<HEADLINE>
Queen Mother launches rowing boat _ without champagne
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   CAMBRIDGE, England (AP) _ The Queen Mother, undaunted by her 97
years and hip surgery less than five months ago, inaugurated a new
rowing boat at Cambridge University on Tuesday, but skipped the
usual champagne launch.
	   At Queens' College, the women's rowing team and sundry VIPs
gathered on the lawn to watch the mother of Queen Elizabeth II
unveil the boat's name _ the Patroness.
	   It was the 50th anniversary of her becoming the college's
patroness, and the 550th anniversary of the college's foundation.
	   The traditional breaking of a bottle on a new ship would damage
a glass fiber boat. So, after the Queen Mother left to have lunch,
the rowers held another brief ceremony to pour a glass of champagne
over the top of the boat for good luck.
	   (acw)
</TEXT>
