<HEADLINE>
Concern over cellular telephone towers, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Concern over cellular telephone towers, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   THE proliferation of cellular telephone communications towers
atop commerical and residential buildings in the State dominated a
major part of yesterday afternoon's sitting, with various
Assemblymen voicing their concerns and displeasure over the issue.
	   Accusations were levelled at State Infrastructure Committee
chairman Datuk Dr Hilmi Yahaya (BN-Teluk Bahang) for the delay on
the part of the authorities in either tearing down the structures
or acting against the telecommunications companies.
	   Proposals were also made for the transmission towers to be sited
in less populated areas such as hilltops.
	   ``Penang Island Muncipal Council enforcement officers have not
been able to dismantle these structures since they involve
high-tension wires,'' he said in reply to points raised during the
debate on a motion of thanks to the Yang di-Pertua Negeri Tun
Hamdan Sheikh Tahir.
	   He said if the structures were to be torn down, mobile phone
users would experience service disruption.
	   ``There has been no conclusive evidence that the non-ionised
radiation emitting from these structures is cancer-causing,'' he
added.
	   Meanwhile, State Technology Committee chairman Datuk Dr Kang
Chin Seng told the House that Government departments and agencies
had already begun making preparations to address the Y2K or
Millennium Bug issue.
	   ``The State Finance, Town and Country Planning and Drainage and
Irrigation departments were found to be problem free, while
potential Y2K probelms in the Land and Mines department, State
Islamic Religious Affairs Department, Penang island and Seberang
Prai municipal councils and the Penang Development Corporation have
already been resolved,'' he added.
	   
