<HEADLINE>
Human error among reasons for diesel spillage, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Human error among reasons for diesel spillage, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   HUMAN error and administrative and machinery faults in the
Penang Water Authority were among the causes of the diesel spillage
at the Lahar Tiang pump station in February this year.
	   State Infrastructure Committee chairman Datuk Dr Hilmi Yahaya
(BN-Teluk Bahang) told the House yesterday, an efficient emergency
response system within the authority could prevent a future
recurrence of the incident.
	   While he did not reveal the identities of those responsible for
the incident, Dr Hilmi told reporters later that disciplinary
action would be taken against the PWA officer who was on duty on
the day of the incident and his immediate supervisor.
	   A report on the investigation of the incident, together with
follow-up measures to ensure the incident does not recur, has been
submitted by the authority to the State Executive Council,'' he
said in reply to points raised during the debate on a motion of
thanks to the Yang di-Pertua Negeri Tun Hamdan Sheikh Tahir for his
opening address.
	   Dr Hilmi said the committee set up to investigate the incident
had also come up with several recommendations to overcome the
weaknesses identified within the PWA.
	   ``These include the need for the PWA to utilise automatic
machinery instead of manual ones.''
	   Other recommendations include: disciplinary action be taken
against officers responsible for the spillage, the need for clear
procedures on the operation of all PWA machinery, written
guidelines from the authority on steps to take in the event of an
emergency at any PWA location, information sessions be conducted by
the PWA at least once a year on emergency response procedures, all
PWA management directives be disseminated to all levels of
employees within the authority; and, surprise checks be conducted
from time to time at all PWA installations to ensure regulations
are adhered to.
	   Meanwhile, Dr Hilmi also said three toll booths - located along
Jalan Prai, Kilometer 9 near Bagan Ajam and the Butterworth-Kulim
Expressway - would be set up for the Butterworth Outer Ring Road.
	   ``Toll charges have not been finalised at this point as the
matter is being discussed between the project concessionaire and
Government authorities,'' he added.
	   
</TEXT>
