<HEADLINE>
Mass copying in some exam centres alleged, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
Mass copying in some exam centres alleged, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Large-scale unfair means has allegedly been going on at the HSC
examinations at different centres of the district.It is gathered
that some corrupt college teachers are allegedly involved in the
act of cheating in the examinations.The centres where free-style
copying is going on are Fulbari Degree College, Rajarhat Mir
Islamail Hossain Degree College and Ulipur Womens College.According
to different sources, like in the past more than half of about 900
examinees of Fulbari Degree College centre are outsiders from
different districts of the region.
	   Most of them allegedly paid Tk 5,000 to Tk 10,000 to some
teachers for free-style copying in the examination halls.A teacher
of Fulbaria Womens college, who was an invigilator at Fulbari
Degree Colleges centre in a written compliant to DC, Kurigram
alleged that he seized answer scripts of two examinees on June 2
last during the Bengali 2nd paper examination for adopting unfair
means. But he could not expel them as the students threatened him
saying that they were appearing in the examination as per contact
with some senior teachers of Fulbari Degree College.
	   Those senior teachers forced the invigilator to return the
answer scripts. They also told the invigilator that they had a
previous agreement to conduct examinations in this way.Local
sources said that six to eight teachers of the said College are
involved in supplying copies to the examinees at the centre. About
one and a half years ago Fulbari examination centre was cancelled
due to massive irregularities. But the college authorities managed
to do away with the cancellation order through political influence,
it is further alleged. Similar allegations have been received from
the other examination centres. Local elite and observers demanded
probe into the unfair means in the examination halls and punishment
to the persons responsible.
	   
