<HEADLINE>
30 litres of cough mixture seized, man detained, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
30 litres of cough mixture seized, man detained, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   SEREMBAN, Mon. - A police team from the State Anti-Narcotics
division today detained a man and seized 30 litres of cough mixture
during a raid in Panchor.
	   Department chief, Deputy Superintendent Zakaria Sudin said the
45-year- old man was allegedly involved in the illegal distribution
of the mixture to addicts.
	   He said acting on a tip-off, the police team raided a house at
Rumah Rakyat Panchor where they found the mixture stored in six
four-litre and two three-litre bottles.
	   ``Police also seized a Proton Wira after discovering another two
small bottles containing the mixture stashed in the car booth.''
	   The man is expected to be charged under Section 32(3) of the
Poisons Act.
	   Under the act, offenders face a maximum RM3,000 fine or a one
year jail term or both if convicted.
	   Zakaria said the police had also handed two men believed to be
dadah pushers who were detained in the State last month, to Pahang
police for further investigation.
	   He said the two, both aged 24, were detained after they were
involved in a road crash at Simpang Keratong in Muadzam Shah,
Pahang on May 25.
	   Zakaria said, after the crash, their car was towed to a workshop
in Bahau where a mechanic found a parcel containing 35 packets with
138 grammes of heroin stashed between the door panels of the Proton
Saga.
	   He said police then detained the two men, one from Terengganu
and another from Kuala Lumpur, who were warded at the Seremban and
Kuala Pilah Hospitals following the crash.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES all rights
reserved as distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
