<SLUG> SMARTONE-TAKES-ON-IFC sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SmarTone takes on IFC network design, HONGKONG STANDARD
</HEADLINE>
SmarTone takes on IFC network design, HONGKONG STANDARD &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   HONGKONG STANDARD
   HONG KONG
   ENGLISH
   Margery TamASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   SMARTONE has taken up a consultancy role for a $70 million
network planning project at the International Finance Centre (IFC),
the telecommunications company said yesterday.
	   SmarTone said it would be responsible for the design and
implementation of part of the telecommunications network at the IFC
in Central.
	   Upon completion of the project, the IFC will be able to support
all 11 mobile communications networks currently in operation in
Hong Kong, enabling quality mobile communications.
	   SmarTone said the equipment supplier for the project was Allen
Telecom, a United States-based telecom equipment manufacturer and
system supplier listed in New York.
	   The project has just commenced and completion is targeted for
August.
	   ``We are excited about this opportunity to apply our
technological knowhow and engineering capabilities to areas beyond
our core business of providing mobile communications services in
Hong Kong,'' Bengt Nordstrom, SmarTone's chief technology officer
said. ``SmarTone will continue to be committed to providing the
most comprehensive mobile communications coverage at major
infrastructure projects to be undertaken in Hong Kong.'' Mr
Nordstrom said a common antenna system, using optic fibre as the
main connection, would be constructed and a total of 140 pairs of
antennas would be installed.
	   
</TEXT>
