<BODY>
<SLUG> SEWAGE-END-UP sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Where does all that sewage end up?, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Where does all that sewage end up?, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   DO you know that we produce five million tonnes of sewage every
year?
	   That's a lot of shit. And all that muck doesn't disappear into
the super- unknown once you've flushed it down the toilet. It
swooshes through underground pipes to sewage treatment plants to be
treated.
	   Since 1993, the entire sewerage system has been privatised to
Indah Water Konsortium. They are the people who are now responsible
for cleaning up your mess.
	   As a service to our readers and to respond to queries from the
public, we will run a weekly question and answer column regarding
your shit, oops, we mean sewage system.
	   Question: How do I know if I am a septic tank customer or a
connected sewerage service customer?
	   Answer: If your sewage flows into a tank before being discharged
to a drain, you are a septic tank customer (diagram A).
	   Septic tanks normally have three or four rectangular metal
covers in a row and in most cases are located at the back of your
premise.
	   These tanks are merely sedimentation tanks that partially treat
sewage.
	   Septic tanks have to be desludged regularly to ensure they
operate efficiently.
	   On the other hand, if your sewage flows indirectly into
underground sewer pipes which carry it to a sewage treatment plant,
you are a connected sewerage service customer (see diagram B).
	   Normally you can identify your property connection pipe (which
you are responsible for) by an inspection chamber which has a metal
cover.
	   The inspection chamber cover is to access the property
connection pipe in instances of blockages.
	   The inspection chamber does not have to be desludged.
	   Q: As a septic tank customer, what sewerage services do I
receive?
	   A: All septic tank customers receive the following services:
regular septic tank desludging and proper and environmentally safe
disposal of the septic tank sludge Q: What services do I receive as
a connected sewerage service customer?
	   A: All connected sewerage customers will receive the following
services: proper maintenance and operations of public sewer
treatment plants where your sewage will be treated; and upkeeping
of public sewer network to ensure that there are no blockages or
broken pipes which can cause sewage backflow and overflowing
manholes.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES all rights
reserved as distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
(PROFILE
(WS SL:SEWAGE-END-UP sked; CT:w; 
(REG:ENGL;)
(LANG:ENGLISH;))
)
