<HEADLINE>
Japan Airlines to offer Tokyo-Las Vegas flights from October
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TOKYO (AP) _ Japan Airlines Co. said Tuesday it will start
flights between Tokyo and Las Vegas on Oct. 2.
	   Las Vegas is Japan Airlines' first new U.S. destination in two
years and the airline's sixth gateway in the continental United
States.
	   The opening of the route follows a revised U.S.-Japan air
agreement giving airlines of both countries opportunities to
expand.
	   Northwest Airlines Corp. became the first airline to provide a
Tokyo-Las Vegas service with the start of its service earlier this
month.
