	   FATHERS have to be given that special recognition for their
endless support and tender loving care for the family.
	   So Hotel Istana Kuala Lumpur has lined up a host of sumptuous
dishes for its High Tea buffet priced at RM37 nett per person at
Taman Sari Brasserie which is set on June 21, a week after the
worldwide celebration of Father's Day.
	   This is to provide an option for those who cannot celebrate the
occasion on June 14.
	   The chefs at the hotel will prepare, among others, variations of
international cold cuts, prawn on ice, Malaysian and international
salads, roasted rib eye with black pepper sauce, steamboat, lamb
chop with light mint-curry sauce, duck breast with grape sauce,
mixed seafood in mussel shell with Morney sauce, salmon fish head
curry with Okra, spicy prawns, marinated fish with Thai chilli and
desserts such as chocolates, ice cream, ais kacang and fresh
fruits.
	   If one prefers Japanese, head for Hotel Istana's Kyoka
Restaurant where lunch and dinner will be offered at RM60 nett and
RM65 nett per person.
	   The buffet consists of a variety of sushi, sashimi, tempura,
furai, teppanyaki, oden, noodles, cold dishes, sukiyaki,
shabu-shabu, mixed salmon rice with pickles and grilled mackerel,
salmon and chicken as well as a wide selection of desserts.
	   Not only that, the hotel will also extend a free lunch to the
celebrated father if dear mum comes with two children.
	   After the hearty meal, take a trip down to its Songket Lounge to
participate in fun activities and competitions such as father and
son look-alike, coke drinking with long straw, a quiz on how well
you know your father, egg frying and lucky draw with attractive
prizes to be won.
	   To complete the celebration, drop by at the hotel's Fitness
Centre for a talk on Dangers of Smoking to be presented by Hospital
Universiti Kebangsaan Malaysia.
	   Sunway Lagoon Resort Hotel in Subang Jaya does not want to be
left out in this once-a-year affair to honour thy father.
	   Its Sun and Surf Cafe offers Father's Day brunch or for a twist
in culinary delight, drop by at Avanti Restaurant to sample dishes
fused from Italian and American flavours.
	   The brunch at the two eateries are priced at RM50 nett per
person. For reservations, call Sun and Surf at 03-5828000 ext 3168
or Avanti Restaurant at ext 3176.
	   At Concorde Shah Alam's Xin Cuisine, set in an opulent dining
area, a feast fit for an emperor will be laid out for the special
dad.
	   The eight-course set menu priced at RM480++ features dishes such
as braised shark's fin soup with cod fish and crab meat, deep fried
barbecue chicken with tong kuei, steamed seabass Nyonya style, and
fried rice with duck meat and chestnut.
	   One can also choose from the RM650++ nine-course set menu for a
table of 10 with dishes such as braised shark's fin with fish maw
and crab meat, deep fried squid paste with black mushroom, pan
fried pomfret with potato and soya sauce, braised mixed vegetables
with bamboo pith, fried rice Fong Wong style, double boiled
sweetened lotus seed with snow fungus and two varieties of sweet
dim sum.
	   Make a date with Xin Cuisine in Concorde Shah Alam at 03-5522200
ext 2221.
	   
</TEXT>
