	   KUALA TERENGGANU, Mon. - Prime Minister Datuk Seri Dr Mahathir
Mohamad is scheduled to arrive on Friday morning in Terengganu for
a half-day visit.
	   Menteri Besar Tan Sri Wan Mokhtar Ahmad said Dr Mahathir would
be briefed on water utilisation and management at the Kepong
treatment plant at 9.30am.
	   Dr Mahathir will perform Friday prayers at Masjid Sultan Zainal
Abidin after which he will have a meeting with heads of department
for about an hour at Sri Iman.
	   Wan Mokhtar said Dr Mahathir would leave for Kuantan at 3.30pm.
	   
