<HEADLINE>
With Sports-Golf-European Money, List
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Westwood shoots to top of European leaderboard

<TEXT>
	   VIRGINIA WATER, England (AP) _ English golfer Lee Westwood moved
from sixth to first on the European Tour money list for the first
time after winning the English Open last Sunday.
	   Westwood, who fired rounds of 68-68-67-68, claimed the winner's
check of 108,330 pounds (dlrs 176,578), bringing his season's
earnings to 383,629 pounds (dlrs 625,315) and taking the top spot
from South African Ernie Els.
	   Westwood has two consecutive tour victories to his credit, after
a one-stroke win in the Open TPC of Europe in Hamburg on June 1. He
also has the lowest score on the European tour this year, a 61 at
Hamburg.
	   Els, who did not play in the English Open, slipped to second
place on the money list with 368,954 (dlrs 601395). Denmark's
Thomas Bjorn dropped into third with 327470 pounds (dlrs 533,776).
	   Sweden's Patrik Sjoland and Scotland's Colin Montgomerie each
moved up one place, into forth and sixth respectively, while
Spaniard Jose Maria Olazabal dropped two places to fifth. (jp)	   
</TEXT>
