<HEADLINE>
Two die, four injured in road crash, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Two die, four injured in road crash, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   SEGAMAT, Mon. - Two people were killed and four others seriously
injured in a road crash involving two cars at Km199 Jalan Johor
Baru-Pekan Batu Anam, near here, at 7.50pm yesterday.
	   The dead were identified as S. Suress Rao, 21, from Rumah Rakyat
Pekan Batu Anam, and one-year-old Siti Noor Syawana from Taman Desa
Indah.
	   Suress, who had head injuries died on the spot, while Siti Noor
Syawana died at 5.30am today at the Sultanah Aminah Hospital in
Johor Baru.
	   Three of the injured were the parents and brother of Siti Noor
Syawana - Razali Mohd Saman, 36, his wife Zanariah Mustafa, 36, and
Mohd Akmal, two.
	   The other survivor was V. Lingam, 23.
	   Segamat deputy district police chief Deputy Superintendent Megat
Amiruddin Megat Wah said Razali, Mohd Akmal and Lingam were sent to
Segamat Hospital and Zanariah to the Sultanah Aminah Hospital in
Johor Baru.
	   He said they were all out of danger.
	   ``The Proton Wira which Lingam was driving was heading for Pekan
Batu Anam from Segamat town when it crashed head on with the Ford
Lancer carrying the family which was coming from the opposite
direction.
	   ``Both cars were badly damaged. Firemen from the Segamat Fire
and Rescue Department took an hour to extricate the victims,'' he
said.
	   
</TEXT>
