<SLUG> BC-Sports-Boxing-Woodhall-Nardiello </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WBC super-middleweight fight set for July 25
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Britain's Richie Woodhall will defend his WBC
super-middleweight title against former champion Vicenzo Nardiello
of Italy on July 25, promoter Frank Warren said Tuesday.
	   Warren said the fight will be held in Italy at a venue still to
be determined.
	   It will be Woodhall's first defense since winning the title in
March with a unanimous decision over South Africa's Thulane ``Sugar
Boy'' Malinga.
	   ``I've got no fear of traveling to Italy,'' Woodhall said. `I
know that I have to knock Nardiello out and that is exactly what I
intend to to.''
	   (sw)	   
