<SLUG> BC-Ukraine-Religion </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Ukrainian believers protest ID codes
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) _ Dozens of Christian Orthodox believers
protested Tuesday against Ukraine's new taxpayer identification
codes, which they claim carry the ``mark of the Antichrist.''
	   The protesters recited prayers and held placards outside the
Ukrainian parliament, demanding the government rescind the new ID
system, the Interfax news agency said.
	   The new taxpayer codes, similar to U.S. Social Security numbers,
became obligatory across Ukraine on Jan. 1.
	   The Holy Synod of the Russian Orthodox Church in Ukraine last
month appealed to President Leonid Kuchma, asking that the system
be changed to accommodate believers' concerns.
	   The appeal noted that many Orthodox faithful consider the code
system, ``not without ground, as the fulfillment of the apocalyptic
prophesy about the mark of the Antichrist.''
	   The Synod proposed that believers be allowed to refuse numbers
that include three or more 6s. The Bible's Book of Revelations
cites 666 as the number of the Antichrist.
	   Some Christians interpret this to mean that the ``mark of the
beast'' could be any identifying number required for official and
business transactions.
	   (str/sms/mr)
</TEXT>
