<HEADLINE>
Futuristic designs on show, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Futuristic designs on show, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   GALERI Tangsi in Jalan Tangsi, Kuala Lumpur is hosting an
exhibition of photography, sculpture and architecture entitled
Beyond Boundaries by Paris-based Malaysian architect Zaini Zainul.
The show will be on until June 26.
	   The launching was held on Saturday with a cocktail reception
attended by French ambassador Edouard Braine who was accompanied by
his wife Chantal.
	   Among the guests at the reception were the gallery's patron
Tunku Abdullah Tunku Abdul Rahman.
	   Others in the guest list were director of Serikandi Pty Ltd
(Australia) Casimah Felix, theatre actor/director Zahim Albakri,
Maria Tan Sri Samad and chief executive officer of Federal Hotel
International Low Gee Tat.
	   Also there were Carol Lim of P&AMP;O Insurance Berhad and her
pianist friend Eddie Chew.
	   Gallery director June Baharuddin said in line with the gallery's
aim to cultivate young and promising talents, it is showcasing 35
of Zaini's original photography works which were previously
exhibited at the Gallery Max-Heler in Cologne (1995) and Gallery
Quicampoix, Paris (1996).
	   June said these works were realised from the award given by two
bodies in the United States - New York Foundation for the Arts and
the National Institute of Architecture Education.
	   She said Penang-born Zaini, a graduate of Colombia University,
New York, has done a series of work in Asia for the past two years,
mainly in Malaysia and Singapore, and his projects are also on
display at the exhibition.
	   
</TEXT>
