	   REFRESHING salads, hearty local and international main courses
and luscious desserts will be available for fathers to savour at
the JW Marriott Hotel Kuala Lumpur's Marriott Cafe come Father's
Day on Sunday.
	   Executive chef Daniel Habermacher and his team recommend
delectable dishes such as assorted cold cuts and terrines, turnip
cake, Hungarian beef goulash, potato with beef bacon cream sauce,
Hong Kong congee with assorted condiments and squid cooked with
lemon grass.
	   The Father's Day buffet is available from noon to 5pm and priced
at RM32++ per person. Children below 12 will be charged RM16++
each. There will be complimentary door gifts courtesy of Moschino
Parfums.
	   At its Man Ho restaurant, chef Lee Yih Shyan's culinary
creations for lunch and dinner include seafood broth with yellow
chives, braised shark's fin with crab meat and conpoy, crispy
roasted Peking duck, stir-fried fresh scallops and asparagus with
black bean sauce in yam basket, among others.
	   The treat is priced at RM69++ to RM89++ per person and fathers
will receive door gifts from Bvlgari Parfums. Call 03-9268520 for
reservations at Marriott Cafe or 03-9268530 for Man Ho.
	   Meanwhile, at Allson Klana Resort in Seremban, the Selera Coffee
House will prepare a variety of appetisers, salads, carvings and
desserts.
	   Its Blossom Court Chinese Restaurant will serve a variety of hot
and cold combinations a la carte while its Waterfall Pool Bar and
Restaurant offers steamboat and barbecue.
	   Call Mahendran of Selera Coffee House, Yok Kek of Blossom Court
or Raja/Hanafi of Waterfall Pool at 06-7629600.
	   At MingCourt Vista Hotel Kuala Lumpur, Father's Day buffet
brunch is served from 11am to 2.30pm and priced at RM 38++ per
adult and RM15.50++ per child under 12.
	   High tea will be served from 3pm to 5pm at RM30++ per adult and
RM15++ per child.
	   Concorde Hotel Kuala Lumpur offers buffet treat at its Melting
Pot Cafe with dishes such as seabass with tom yam sauce, beef
medallion with peppercorn sauce, lamb kuzi, paupiette of salmon and
zucchini and steamed or roast chicken rice as well as desserts such
as cheesecake, banana franzipan, tiramisu cake and coffee mousse.
	   Quiz winners will walk away with prizes and door gifts await all
guests.
	   Call 03-2442200 ext 2337 (Melting Pot) or Xin Cuisine at
03-2448750 for reservations.
	   
