<HEADLINE>
School sends in 656 Future Grads entries, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
School sends in 656 Future Grads entries, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   IPOH, Mon. - SK Methodist (ACS) today sent in 656 entries for
the Kuala Lumpur Mutual Fund Future Grads contest.
	   School principal Lai Kum Mung presented the entries to KLMF Ipoh
senior branch manager Foong Kuan Mun at the school.
	   Lai said every one of the 434 pupils in Standards Five and Six,
to whom the contest was open, took part.
	   ``The boys were very excited about the contest as it was a way
of increasing their general knowledge while offering them a chance
to win attractive prizes for themselves as well as for their
school,'' said Lai.
	   One of Ipoh's premier schools, SK Methodist has five Standard
Five classes and six Standard Six classes.
	   Lai said the school stressed English Language proficiency.
	   ``One of our programmes is an English Day on Fridays where the
school assembly is conducted in English and pupils are encouraged
to speak only English on that day.''
	   English teacher Coreen Chow said the pupils' command of English
was relatively good, comparable to the standards of larger and more
established schools in the country.
	   
</TEXT>
