   June 09, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   MALACCA, Mon. - The Malaysian Maritime Academy in Kuala Sungai
Baru should offer more courses including port management, marine
environment management and international trade, Chief Minister
Datuk Seri Abu Zahar Isnin said today.
	   Speaking at the graduation ceremony for 130 students of the
academy, Abu Zahar said the academy should keep abreast of rapid
changes in maritime.
	   ``It should also ensure the syllabus is constantly updated and
improved.''
	   He said the academy's privatisation would help make it more
efficient.
	   Ahmad Nazulan Abdul Razak received the Prime Minister's award
for being the best overall graduate this year.
	   
