<HEADLINE>
Ministry gives thumbs up for franchised courses, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Ministry gives thumbs up for franchised courses, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KOTA BARU, Mon. - The Education Ministry is satisfied with the
quality of matriculation courses which have been franchised to
colleges by public universities.
	   The ministry's higher learning division director, Professor
Hassan Said, said private colleges had shown an improvement in the
standards which were required for the programme to be conducted.
	   ``However, this cannot be successful if they fail to adhere
strictly to the conditions which have been laid down by the
university authorities.
	   ``Among the conditions are that the colleges should prepare
various facilities for students. They include lodgings, lecture
theatres, lecturers and suitable supervision,'' he told reporters
after opening the Fourth National Conference on Medical Sciences at
Universiti Sains Malaysia Hospital in Kubang Kerian today.
	   Also present were USM research and development vice-chancellor
Professor Jamjam Rajikan and the campus director of USM Kelantan,
Professor Roslani Abdul Majid.
	   Hassan said the colleges were being monitored by two authorities
- the private education division and the respective universities
which were franchising the courses.
	   He said the ministry was now conducting a study to upgrade the
franchise system, and this included the matriculation programme.
	   In his speech earlier, Hassan praised USM for taking the
initiative in emphasising the use of information technology in
education, which could assist students in their studies.
	   
