<SLUG> BC-Czech-EBRD,0148 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EBRD announces investment in Czech savings bank
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PRAGUE, Czech Republic (AP) _ The European Bank for
Reconstruction and Development acquired an 11.8 percent stake in
Ceska Sporitelna, the Czech Republic's largest savings bank, EBRD
said Tuesday.
	   The stake, valued at 2.5 billion koruna (dlrs 75.8 million),
represents the largest ever single equity investment by the EBRD,
the bank said in a statement.
	   The Czech state's 45 percent stake in Ceska Sporitelna remains
unaffected, it said.
	   The EBRD is a development bank established in 1991 to help the
post-communist countries in central and eastern Europe in their
transition fromas centrally planned to a market economy.
	   EBRD said it is buying the share in Ceska Sporitelna to enhance
its attractiveness to foreign investors ahead of its possible
complete privatization next year.
</TEXT>
