<BODY>
<SLUG> UMNO-GENERAL-ASSEMBLY sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Only two resolutions to be tabled at Umno general assembly, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Only two resolutions to be tabled at Umno general assembly, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Mon. - Umno secretary-general Datuk Sabbaruddin
Chik said only two resolutions will be tabled at this year's Umno
general assembly which begins on June 18.
	   He said these were the debate on the presidential address and
the economy.
	   In the past, among the resolutions tabled were on religion,
education and the economy.
	   He said the move was to allow the delegates to have more time
for debate. ``Each delegate will also be given five minutes extra
during debating time,'' he said adding that delegates will also be
allowed to touch on religious and educational issues during debate.
	   Previously, delegates were given 10 minutes each to debate. Many
had complained that this was insufficent.
	   Sabbaruddin was speaking to reporters after briefing all Umno
state liaison and divisional secretaries and information heads on
the coming general assembly at the Putra World Trade Centre.
	   He said a total of 1,910 delegates, including permanent
chairman, deputy permanent chairman and the Supreme Council
members, would be attending the assembly.
	   
</TEXT>
