<SLUG> BC-Weather Summary,0990 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands from
the National Weather Service.
	   Rainfall amounts on Monday ranged from one to two inches in the
interior to one-quarter of an inch along the coasts.
	   A high-pressure ridge to the north of Puerto Rico will slowly
drift south through Wednesday. This high-pressure ridge will ensure
a drier-than-normal weather regime through Wednesday and slightly
higher-than-normal temperatures.
	   A trough of low pressure in the westerlies will arrive late
Thursday from the north, resulting in an unsettled weather pattern
during the end of the week and the upcoming weekend.
	   San Juan and the northern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Partly cloudy. Breezy in the afternoon. A 30 percent
chance of showers. High 85 to 90. Wind northeast 15 to 20 mph.
Gusty in the afternoon.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy in the east, with a 20 percent chance
of showers. Fair in the west. Low 75 to 80. Wind east at 5 to 10
mph.
	   Wednesday... Partly cloudy. A 20 percent chance of showers. High
around 90. Wind northeast at 15 mph.
	   Eastern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Variable cloudiness in the morning. Partly cloudy and
breezy in the afternoon. A 30 percent chance of showers, mainly in
the morning. High 85 to 90. Wind east at 10 to 20 mph and gusty in
the afternoon.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Low 75 to 80. Wind east 5 to 10 mph.
	   Wednesday... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of showers.
High from 85 to 90. Wind east 15 to 20 mph.
	   Ponce and the southern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Partly cloudy in the morning. Variable cloudiness in
the afternoon with a 40 percent chance of showers. Possible
afternoon thunderstorms inland. High around 90. Wind southeast 10
to 15 mph.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy in the east with a slight chance of
showers. Fair in the west. Low 75 to 80. Wind light from the
northeast. Chance of rain is less than 20 percent.
	   Wednesday... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of showers.
Possible thunderstorms inland in the afternoon. High around 90.
Wind southeast 10 to 15 mph.
	   Mayaguez and the western sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Mostly sunny in the morning. Increasing cloudiness in
the afternoon with a 50 percent chance of showers and
thunderstorms. High 85 to 90. Wind east at 10 to 20 mph except for
an afternoon sea breeze less than 10 mph along the west coast.
	   Tonight... Decreasing clouds with showers ending. Becoming fair
by midnight. Low 65 to 75. Chance of rain is less than 20 percent.
Wind east 5 to 10 mph.
	   Wednesday... Mostly sunny in the morning. Variable cloudiness in
the afternoon with a 50 percent chance of showers and
thunderstorms. High 85 to 90. Wind east 15 to 20 mph except for a
weak west wind less than 10 mph along the west coast in the
afternoon.
	   Interior sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Partly cloudy in the morning. Variable cloudiness in
the afternoon with a 40 percent chance of showers. Isolated
thunderstorms in the far west. Breezy in the afternoon. High from
75 to 80 in the mountains, 85 to 90 in lower elevations. Wind
northeast at 15 to 20 mph.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy in the east with a 20 percent chance of
showers. Fair in the west. Low 65 to 70 in the mountains to 70 to
75 in lower valleys. Wind northeast near 10 mph.
	   Wednesday... Partly cloudy in the morning. Variable cloudiness
in the afternoon with a 30 percent chance of showers. Possible
afternoon thunderstorm in the far west. High from 75 to 80 in the
mountains to 85 to 90 in lower elevations. Wind northeast at 10 to
15 mph.
	   St. Thomas, St. John and the Adjacent Islands-St. Croix:
	   Today... Partly cloudy. Breezy in the afternoon. A 30 percent
chance of showers, mainly in the morning. High around 90. Wind east
at 15 to 20 mph.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of showers.
Low near 80. Wind northeast at 10 to 15 mph.
	   Wednesday... Partly sunny. A 20 percent chance of showers. High
around 90. Wind northeast at 15 mph.
	   Atlantic waters north and northeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   Small craft should exercise caution.
	   This afternoon... Wind east 15 to 20 kt. Near shore waters seas
3 to 4 ft. Offshore seas 4 to 5 ft. Widely scattered showers.
	   Tonight... Wind northeast 15 to 20 kt. Near shore waters seas 3
to 4 ft. Offshore seas 4 to 5 ft. Widely scattered to isolated
showers.
	   Wednesday... Wind northeast to east at 15 to 20 kt. Seas 3 to 5
ft. Isolated to widely scattered showers.
	   Caribbean waters south and southeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   Small craft should exercise caution.
	   This afternoon... Wind east at 15 to 20 kt. Near shore waters
seas 3 to 4 ft. Off shore seas 4 to 5 ft. Widely scattered showers.
Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tonight... Wind east at 15 to 20 kt. Near shore seas 3 to 4 ft.
Offshore seas 4 to 5 ft. Widely scattered showers.
	   Wednesday... Wind east 15 to 20 kt. Seas 3 to 5 ft. Widely
scattered showers.
	   Near shore waters of western Puerto Rico:
	   This afternoon... Wind east 10 to 15 kt, except variable less
than 10 kt along the coast. Seas 2 to 3 ft. Widely scattered
showers. Isolated afternoon thunderstorms.
	   Tonight... Wind east at 5 to 10 kt. Seas 2 ft. Isolated showers.
	   Wednesday... Wind northeast 10 to 15 kt. Seas 2 to 3 ft. Widely
scattered showers. Isolated afternoon thunderstorms.
	   Outlook for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands waters:
	   Wednesday night through Saturday... Wind east at 20 kt or less.
Seas 5 ft or less.
</TEXT>
