<HEADLINE>
Toilets with a touch of difference, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Toilets with a touch of difference, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 07, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   THEME TOILETS ... It's nice for a change to find attractive
toilets like these located at the Panti Tropical Fruit Farm, 30km
from Kota Tinggi.
	   Travellers to and from Mersing and Tanjung Leman, who stop at
the rest station of the farm, find them a pleasant change.
	   The toilets, in mock log cabin style, are surrounded by
well-landscaped walkways. The builders, in line with the fruit farm
concept, have crafted two coconut sculptures for the roof of each
toilet.
	   The ``coconuts'' are fitted with water fountains resembling
coconut water pouring into a pool.
	   The fountain is not yet functioning as the farm resort is still
without electricity supply.
	   Panti Fruit Farm area manager Rashid Jusoh said the farm, which
was set up by Felcra Bhd, was in its first phase of development
with the building of fruit stalls, a restaurant, surau and rest
areas.
	   The 637ha fruit farm has durian, starfruit, cempedak, jackfruit
and honey lemon trees.
	   Chalets, fishing and recreational facilities will be put up in
the future.
	   
</TEXT>
