<SLUG> TEMPORARY-SHELTER-SOON sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Temporary shelter for homeless natives soon, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Temporary shelter for homeless natives soon, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 07, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KUCHING, Sat. - A temporary shelter will soon be built near the
proposed Bakun Hydroelectric Dam resettlement area in Sungai Asap
to house the 521 natives who lost their longhouse in Long Linau,
Belaga, to fire last Saturday.
	   Bakun Resettlement and Social Economy Committee chairman Dr
James Masing said a special committee headed by the Resident of
Kapit had been set up to look into the matter.
	   ``We will move the affected longhouse folks as soon as possible.
But the place to resettle them is not within the proposed Bakun
resettlement area,'' he said.
	   Masing was speaking at the Sarawak General Hospital today, after
accompanying Yang diPertua Negeri Tun Ahmad Zaidi Adruce Muhammed
Noor on a visit to the children's ward. The visit was in
conjunction with the Yang diPertuan Agong Tuanku Ja'afar's
birthday.
	   The 82-door Rumah Uma Nyaving, one of the longhouses which will
be submerged by the now postponed Bakun dam, caught fire about 7pm
when many of its inhabitants were busy preparing for Gawai Dayak
which was celebrated on June 1 and 2.
	   The villagers' quick action prevented eight rooms from being
destroyed by the fire which was believed to have been caused by a
short circuit.
	   Masing said the villagers were now living in makeshift huts or
with relatives in the eight rooms. Loss was estimated at RM950,000.
	   
</TEXT>
