	   JOHOR BARU, Sat. - The State Government has identified 14,000
underprivileged people in need of Government aid in Johor.
	   They include the disabled, orphans, single mothers, the poor and
senior citizens.
	   State Executive Councillor Halimah Sadique said the State Social
Welfare department was finalising a profile of them.
	   ``This is to enable the State to have a systematic access to
information when planning programmes, such as training and
rehabilitation for the underprivileged,'' she said after
officiating at a charity show today.
	   Halimah, who is also State Unity, Women Affairs and Social
Welfare Committee chairman was representing Menteri Besar Datuk
Abdul Ghani Othman.
	   She also launched the ``Mohd Amirul Hakeem Fund'' homepage to
collect funds for the two-year-old neuro patient.
	   
