	   KOTA KINABALU, Sat. - Chief Minister Tan Sri Bernard Giluk
Dompok has called on chambers of commerce in Sabah to pool their
resources to effectively weather the economic downturn.
	   He said close co-operation among chambers of commerce was vital
to ensure the business community continued to make positive
contributions towards the development of the State.
	   ``I hope the existing co-operation among chambers of commerce in
the State will continue to be enhanced,'' he said at the
Kadazandusun Chamber of Commerce and Industry (KCCI) installation
of office bearers here last night.
	   Also present were KCCI president Datuk Ajit Andrew Galun, Sabah
Bumiputera Chamber of Commerce president Datuk Musa Aman and Sabah
United Chinese Chambers of Commerce president Datuk Sari Tan Nuar.
	   The State Government, Dompok said, would like to see chambers of
commerce play a leading role in establishing more joint venture
projects between local and foreign firms.
	   Dompok gave an assurance that the State Government would
continue to support efforts by the chambers to encourage business
collaborations between Bumiputera and non-Bumiputera entrepreneurs.
	   
