<SLUG> THAKSIN-LAUNCHES sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Thaksin launches new-party media blitz, NATION
</HEADLINE>
Thaksin launches new-party media blitz, NATION &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   NATION
   THAILAND
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   TYCOON Thaksin Shinawatra, living up to the local adage that
''if you have something to say, say it loudly'', has done it again.
This time he has launched a media blitz, taking out full-page
display advertisements to unveil his new political party.
	   Under the slogan ''New Constitution: new thinking, new doing for
every Thai'', Thaksin presented himself, or what critics called
Thaksin Inc, as a catalyst to form the new party.
	   In keeping with the pledge for a broad-based party, people will
Tuesday be asked to mail in their suggestions for the party name.
	   Among the suggested names are Nawathai (New Thai), Prachatham
(People's Justice), Thai Rak Thai (Thais-love-Thais), Prachakom
(Community) and Raksthai (Thai Guardian).
	   Respondents to the advertisements are also requested to outline
their thoughts on the party platform.
	   Without a ready platform, Thaksin displayed a picture of himself
in a forward-looking pose with the country's flag in the
background, as evidence of his leadership.
	   
</TEXT>
