<HEADLINE>
Best-selling book `Sophie's World' now a musical
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: ADDS description of book in last graf &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   ETTLINGEN, Germany (AP) _ ``Sophie's World'' is going from the
page to the stage _ as a musical.
	   Organizers of a summer festival in Ettlingen, in southwest
Germany, announced Tuesday that their ``compressed version'' of
Jostein Gaarder's global best seller would have its world premiere
Friday.
	   Gisle Kverndokk wrote the music and Oystein Wiik the text. The
musical will be performed through Aug. 23.
	   ``Sophie's World,'' a thinly veiled philosophy primer, had sold
more than 10 million copies in 42 languages.
