<HEADLINE>
World Cup: Italian striker is sick
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: will be UPDATED &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   SENLIS, France (AP) _ Italian striker Fabrizio Ravanelli,
suffering from fever and cough, on Tuesday was taken to a hospital
to undergo X-ray examinations to determine if he's suffering from a
bronchitis, team officials said.
	   The sudden illness of the 29-year-old forward of Olympique
Marseille may cause his last-minute exclusion from Italy's World
Cup team and the possible inclusion of Parma's forward Enrico
Chiesa.
	   Chiesa is in France as Italy's 23rd player and still could be
named in Italy's list.
	   World Cup teams can report to FIFA replacement of sick or
injured players through 1530 GMT Wednesday _ the kickoff time of
the World Cup's inaugural match between Brazil and Scotland.
	   ``Team doctors are going to report to Cesare Maldini the outcome
of examinations and the coach will take a decision,'' team
spokesman Antonello Valentini said.
	   Ravanelli's illness was the last bout of misfortune to hit the
Italian team.
	   Star-forward Alessandro Del Piero has only just recovered from a
right thigh strain and is out of Italy's first match against Chile
on Thursday.
	   Defender Moreno Torricelli bruised his right foot in training 10
days ago and resumed practicing on Tuesday.
	   Chiesa had been put on alert as a substitute for Del Piero first
and then Torricelli. Now he had a third chance to stay with the
team.
	   (pv-jw)
</TEXT>
