<SLUG> JALAN-UNIVERSITI-CLOSED sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
A section of Jalan Universiti to be closed, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
A section of Jalan Universiti to be closed, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 07, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   PETALING JAYA, Sat. - A section of Jalan Universiti, from the
International Islamic University to Universiti Hospital, will be
closed to traffic from Monday until Oct 8 for pipe-laying works.
	   The closure would be carried out in three stages, with each
taking up 150 to 200 metres of the road.
	   According to a Press release by Puncak Niaga (M) Sdn Bhd, one
side of the road would be closed to traffic.
	   Excavation and pipe-laying works, part of Phase Two of the
Sungai Selangor Water Supply Scheme, would be carried out
round-the-clock, including on Saturdays and Sundays.
	   ``As work will be done in three stages, stretches which are not
affected will be opened to traffic under normal conditions,'' the
statement said.
	   The first stage, from Monday until July 8, would stretch from
the junction of Jalan 17/1 to the university roundabout.
	   For the second stage - from July 9 to 23 - work would centre
around the roundabout.
	   The third stage, between July 24 and Oct 8, would involve work
from the roundabout to the hospital.
	   Signs would be placed along the road to inform the public on
traffic conditions.
	   Any queries should be forwarded to Puncak Niaga's Corporate
Communications Department at 03-2018648 or fax 03-2384386.
	   
</TEXT>
