	   KUALA LUMPUR, Sat. - National Institute of Occupational Safety
and Health executive chairman Datuk Lee Lam Thye has urged
companies to send representatives to a conference jointly organised
with the Malaysian Insurance Institute.
	   The conference, themed ``Managing Life, Health and Safety Risks
in the Changing Environment'', will be held on June 10 and 11 at
the Concorde Hotel. It will bring together 42 industry leaders to
discuss issues relating to safety and health at the workplace.
	   ``Company management should realise that safety and health
cannot be compromised despite the current economic slowdown,'' Lee
said.
	   Among the speakers at the conference are Lee, the
director-general of the Department of Occupational Safety and
Health, Zakaria Nanyan, and his deputy, Abu Bakar Che Man, Liberty
Risk Services Malaysia Sdn Bhd managing director Dr Jaswant Singh,
Malaysian Insurance Institute consultant Azman Ismail and WorkSafe
Western Australia Commissioner Neil Bartholomaeus.
	   
