<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Chelsea-Desailly </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Chelsea signs French AC Milan star
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Chelsea on Tuesday completed its second
international signing in 24 hours as French World Cup star Marcel
Desailly joined the Blues in a 4.6 million pound (dlrs 7.5 million)
deal.
	   The deal for the AC Milan defender and midfielder was completed
at the French World Cup training camp, just hours after Chelsea
signed Spanish international and Barcelona right back Albert
Ferrer.
	   The signing brings Gianluca Vialli's Cup Winners' Cup holders'
spending to more than 12 million pounds (dlrs 19.56 million) in the
last two weeks.
	   Lazio's Pierluigi Casiraghi was signed for 5.4 million pounds
(dlrs 8.8 million) two weeks ago, with confirmation of Danish
international Brian Laudrup's transfer from Glasgow Rangers finally
coming Monday.
	   Desailly, who has won 41 caps for France, said he was looking
forward to the challenge of playing in the Premier League after
five years in Serie A.
	   ``I'm happy and it's an important thing in my career to go and
play in England,'' he told the club's telephone hot line. ``It was
a big decision to leave Milan where I've played for five years, but
Chelsea are in the Cup Winners' Cup and they are a club that's
growing.''
	   (jp/sw) 	   
</TEXT>
