<TEXT>
	   MONTREAL (AP) _ An explosion, possibly from a gas leak,
shattered a shelter for homeless people in Montreal on Tuesday,
injuring about 30 people as they were about to eat lunch.
	   Police said five of those injured were seriously hurt.
	   Witnesses said there was a strong smell of gas before the
explosion, which occurred about 12:15 p.m. (1615 GMT). 	   
