<HEADLINE>
Green Channel to open branch office in Sylhet shortly, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
Green Channel to open branch office in Sylhet shortly, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
   L.H. SharifASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Green Channel tour operator will open a branch office in Sylhet
shortly. This will be the company's third branch office. With its
head office in Chittagong, Green Channel has two other branch
offices in Dhaka and Cox's Bazar.The only deep sea-cruise package
tour operator in Bangladesh, Green Channel operated eleven
sea-cruise package tour programmes last season.Green Channel
operates sea-cruise programmes during October and March when the
sea is calm and quiet. Before every trip to the sea they place
several ads in national dailies so that intending participants can
make advance booking. The charge for a package sea-cruise programme
that lasts for seven to eight hours is Tk 500 per person.
	   The charge is inclusive of breakfast, packet lunch prepared in
the vessel's kitchen and afternoon tea and snacks. It also includes
complimentary soft drinks throughout the sea-cruise programme and
live band show concerts. Besides, Green Channel operates study tour
programmes for college and university students to India, Nepal and
Bhutan by road through Jessore's Benapole border. The charge for
the 14 to 19-day package study tour programme is Tk 8,500 per
person. Domestically Green Channel operates 1 to 5-day package tour
programmes covering all the attractive tourist spots of the
country. The charge for the package tour programme depends on
distance and duration of each of the programmes. At the moment,
Green Channel has four 12-seater micro-buses of which one is
airconditioned.
	   For sea-cruising they hire luxury vessels from the public sector
IWTC (Inland Water Transport Corporation). ``I read a report about
a private inbound package tour operator in weekly Bichitra sometime
in early 1992 and inspired by the tour operator I and my business
associates decided to launch a package tour operating company that
would mostly promote domestic tourism''. said Selim Ahmed, one of
the promoter directors of Green Channel, while talking to this
correspondent at their Chittagong headquarters at the new
Chittagong railway station terminal building on June 3.Accordingly
the company was launched and green channel organised its maiden
sea-cruise voyage on 25 December, 1992.
	   
</TEXT>
