<SLUG> BC-Israel-Yassin,0305 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Hamas: Sheik Yassin to return within days
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   GAZA CITY, Gaza Strip (AP) _ The founder and spiritual leader of
the radical Islamic group Hamas, will return to Gaza within days, a
spokesman said Tuesday.
	   Sheik Ahmed Yassin, who has been on a 3 1/2-month tour of Muslim
countries raising millions of dollars and drumming up support for
Hamas, will ``most likely'' come back to Gaza on Saturday, Mahmoud
Zahar, a Hamas spokesman, told The Associated Press.
	   Israel's security establishment and political leaders have been
debating for weeks whether Yassin would pose a greater danger
inside or outside of Gaza. Israel, which controls Gaza's borders,
could keep Yassin out if it wished.
	   Israeli leaders appeared Tuesday to be leaning toward allowing
him back, in part because keeping him out could prompt more
violence from backers of Hamas.
	   ``The choice is not between what is good and better, but between
what is bad and worse,'' Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu told
Israel radio.
	   State-owned Israel TV reported that Israel's internal security
agency, Shin Bet, submitted its recommendation to the government
that Yassin be allowed to returned and coordinated with the
Palestinian Authority.
	   Hamas opposes peace with Israel. Its military wing has killed
more than 100 Israelis in scores of attacks. The group's popularity
in the Palestinian lands, especially Gaza, is seen as a growing
threat to Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat's authority.
	   Yassin's fiery comments on his tour, such as his description of
suicide attacks as ``holy missions,'' have been widely reported in
Israel.
	   Yassin was freed from an Israeli jail last fall to buy the
freedom of two Israeli Mossad agents captured in Jordan during a
bungled assassination attempt on another Hamas leader. 	   
</TEXT>
