<HEADLINE>
Russian star gets Wimbledon wild card
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   WIMBLEDON, England (AP) _ Russian teenager Marat Safin, who
reached the French Open quarterfinals as a qualifier, has been
granted a wild card for Wimbledon.
	   The 18-year-old Safin, who had wins over Andre Agassi and
defending champion Gustavo Kuerten in Paris, was the only
non-British player to receive one of the five wild cards announced
Tuesday.
	   Three more wild cards are available for the men's singles, with
Boris Becker among those who could benefit. Becker, who had
announced his retirement from Grand Slam tennis at last year's
Wimbledon, has said he will decide by Friday whether to enter
Wimbledon again.
	   The other four players given wild cards Tuesday were Britain's
Chris Wilkinson, Andrew Richardson, Mark Petchey and Danny
Sapsford.
	   Five of the eight wild cards for the women's singles were also
awarded, all to Britons _ Samantha Smith, Karen Cross, Lorna
Woodroffe, Julie Pullin and Jo Ward.
	   (sw)	   
</TEXT>
