<HEADLINE>
Local EDI provider named, NATION
</HEADLINE>
Local EDI provider named, NATION &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   NATION
   THAILAND
   ENGLISH
   JIRAPAN BOONNOONASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   GE SIAM Information Service, an EDI (Electronic Data
Interchange) provider, has appointed Thai Electronic Commerce
Service (ITECS) as its exclusive distributor to provide electronic
commerce products in Thailand.
	   The products for sale include shipping, retail and banking
products. However, the trading product is expected to be its most
popular.
	   ''Trading is a business which has to deal directly with the
Customs Department. We will sell a total product from PC to
mainframe at between Bt100 to Bt300 per licence,'' said Ittiwatr
Srinarongsiri, the company's managing director.
	   In addition, the company plans to sell value-added services such
as increasing the speed of links between local and international
companies.
	   He said to reduce the cost of software investment, the firm will
customise international software in Thai editions. By the third
quarter of this year, the firm will launch three to four software
items in Thai edition.
	   ''We have products for Internet EDI but the market is not mature
yet. In addition, we plan to offer electronic commerce,'' he said.
	   As a Trade Siam partner, the company will be responsible for
implementing software and hardware, training, consultation and
transfer of knowledge to build and operate the Thailand National
EDI Centre, while Trade Siam will organise management of the
facility. 
</TEXT>
