<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Canada-Shelter Explosion, 1st Ld-Writethru,0165 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Blast destroys homeless shelter in Montreal; about 30 hurt
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; EDS: UPDATES with two people reported missing, other details. &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   MONTREAL (AP) _ An explosion, possibly from a gas leak,
shattered a shelter for homeless people in Montreal on Tuesday,
injuring about 30 people as they were about to eat lunch.
	   One person was in critical condition and five others were in
serious condition, police said. Two staff members _ a nun and a
volunteer cook _ were reported missing.
	   The explosion sheared off one entire wall of the three-story
stone building, spilling rubble into the street in historic Old
Montreal. Firefighters were searching through the debris, unsure if
anyone was trapped underneath.
	   Witnesses said there was a strong smell of gas before the
explosion, which occurred about 12:15 p.m. (1615 GMT).
	   No one lived in the shelter _ it was used to provide meals and
shelter for homeless people during the day. 	   
</TEXT>
