<SLUG> BC-Russia-Teachers' Protest </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Siberian teachers take official hostage to demand back wages
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Teachers in Siberia are holding a local
administration chief in his office to demand months of unpaid
wages, a news agency reported Tuesday.
	   Teachers from the Maiminsk region said they would not allow the
administration chief, Pyotr Burlakov, to leave until their wages
and child subsidies are paid, the ITAR-Tass news agency reported.
	   It said the teachers have barricaded the office for two days.
	   Earlier this year, workers from a Siberian coal mine held the
mine's director and other officials hostage for several days to
demand years of unpaid wages.
	   Neither protest involved violence. During the miners' protest,
several supposed hostages stayed with the workers voluntarily, even
after they were told they were free to leave.
