	   REPUTATION AT STAKE ... Way back in 1993 Malacca town was known
as the cleanest town in Malaysia.
	   Such a recognition from the Housing and Local Government
Ministry will not last long if this picture is anything to go by.
	   Residents of Taman Ayer Molek do not seem to appreciate efforts
by the Malacca Municipal Council to maintain cleanliness within the
town area.
	   Although a large rubbish bin is available, it is left empty. The
residents prefer to throw rubbish at an undesignated spot next to
the bin.
	   A warning sign at the spot goes unheeded.
	   The residents' attitude seems to be at odds with the council's
slogan ``Malacca Boleh dan Bersih Indah''.
	   If such an attitude prevails, the town's image will go down the
drain.
	   
</TEXT>
