	   AN arts and craft exhibition featuring works by art teachers
will be held from today till Friday between 10am and 6pm at the
concourse area of the 1 Utama Shopping Complex in Petaling Jaya.
	   The event is in conjunction with the Selangor Teachers' Day
celebration.
	   Themed Lorekan Seni Gurisan Jiwa, the exhibition features 300
pieces by 36 art teachers from 39 secondary schools in Petaling
District.
	   The works are also for sale.
	   Among the pieces on display are paintings, drawings, ceramic
work, khat, metal work, batik, woodcut and coral clay, with prices
ranging from RM200 to RM5,000 apiece.
	   Petaling District education officer Soleha Othman said the
exhibition would be officiated at by Education Minister Datuk Seri
Najib Tun Razak at 11am today.
	   She added that the exhibition could give teachers a chance to
show their masterpieces.
	   Soleha added that at the same time, the exhibition would give
teachers a chance to sell sell their work for additional income.
	   
