	   FATHER'S Day celebration at the Kuala Lumpur Hilton is given a
different twist this year.
	   On Sunday, the hotel invites fathers to join in the fun and
games with the whole family with an event themed Dad Goes Wild Wild
West.
	   Guests are requested to come in jeans or cowboy hats as there
will be prizes for those who come dressed to theme.
	   For dining and entertainment, the Planter's Inn and Fic's
Restaurant and Wine Bar have planned a wide range of tempting
delights for the whole family.
	   Start the celebration with a country and western brunch at RM52
nett per person at the Planter's Inn which offers smoked salmon,
waffles, pancakes, salmon omelette, mini burgers, French fries,
chicken wings, hot dogs and more.
	   The Fic's brunch is priced at RM59 nett per person and comes
with aglass of wine or juice.
	   For dinner, Fic's offer an ala carte menu with dishes such as
pan-fried fritter sweet duck liver, tender braised lamb shank,
Australian beef sirloin and more.
	   Wine lovers get to enjoy a wide selection of wines and the
dinner set menu costs RM72 nett per person.
	   The Planter's Inn features buffet dinner with local flavours for
the more conventional dads. Priced at RM48 nett per person, diners
can savour selections such as satay, roti canai, ulam, rendang,
curries and ikan bakar, just to name a few.
	   In addition, dads will receive exclusive cigars for dining
pleasure at both the outlets, courtesy of Bradshaw Tobacco.
	   There will be lots of door gifts and prizes for the children.
	   Games include cowboy tug-of-war, best dressed cowboy and
cowgirl, horse riding games and card drawing contest.
	   Children under 12 years will be charged at 50 per cent of the
buffet price.
	   All diners are also entitled to participate in a Wild Wild West
quiz which offers fantastic prizes.
	   For reservations call 02-2482322.
	   Pan Pacific Glenmarie Resort's Kites 24-hour dining restaurant
features a high tea buffet, offering local and international
favourites.
	   Its executive chef Koh Boon Seng and his team have specially
prepared a menu of sumptuous spread comprising among others
assorted sushi boat, kerabu kerang, asam laksa, pizza, mango fried
rice to cakes and pastries.
	   The buffet is priced at RM28++ per adult and RM14++ per child
aged four to 12 years and is available from 3.30pm to 6pm.
	   Call Taufik and his team at 03-7031000 ext 7320/1 for details.
	   At Wenworth Hotel Kuala Lumpur's Wenworth Court, themed food
promotions for five persons at RM233++ and RM368++ or for 10
persons at RM398++ and RM588++ have been planned on June 20 and 21
for Father's Day.
	   Menu highlights include braised shark's fin soup with assorted
dried seafood, steamed cod fish with soya sauce, and baked tiger
prawn with belacan and crispy garlic.
	   Its Palms Court on the other hand, offers high tea brunch at
RM21++ for adults and RM15++ per child age four to 12 and is
available on June 21.
	   A complimentary cake will be given to the father with every
booking for 10 persons or more.
	   Hyatt Regency Saujana will make fathers feel special by
preparing a lavish spread of buffet lunch-cum-high tea at Suria
Cafe.
	   Items offered include a variety of cold platter, salads, soup
and local and Western delicacies.
	   Served from noon to 4.30pm, the buffet spread is priced at
RM42.55 nett for adults and RM21.30 nett for children.
	   For reservations, call Tony Ganesan at 03-7405270 or 7461234 ext
4070.
	   
