	   FOURTEEN students who received bursaries from the Lion-ASM
Foundation Scholarship or educational loans can now stop worrying
about their finances.
	   The four students who were offered scholarships will receive
RM5,000 per annum while the others will get loans of RM4,000 per
annum.
	   The presentation was held at Menara Lion in Jalan Ampang.
	   Lion Group director Datuk Murad Hashim and group human resources
assistant general manager Herbert Lobo presented the scholarships
and loans to the students.
	   The scholarship recipients were Shirleen Ng Shook Yin, K.
Savaranan, Lim Chin Ling and Noraliza Abdul Halim. Among the loan
recipients were Margaret Tang Siew Peng, Yap Choon Seng, Loh Wern
Chern, Yew Poh Leong, Pho Jin Lian and Swa Beng Wei.
	   Nine other students who are doing their pre-university courses
also received awards worth RM500 each for two years.
	   Meanwhile, 17 children of employees who excelled in last year's
Sijil Pelajaran Malaysia and Peperiksaan Menengah Rendah
examinations were not forgotten as they each received a book prize
worth RM500.
	   Murad said it was the eighth year running that the foundation
presented awards to deserving students since it was launched in
1985.
	   He said to date Lion had sponsored 229 students through various
sponsorships worth RM4.1 million.
	   ``We received about 800 applications for the scholarships. We
had a tough time selecting the deserving applicants,'' he said.
	   He added that it had been the Lion Group's aspiration to
continue contributing to the country's educational and human
resources development in line with Vision 2020.
	   Murad said the group hoped to build a highly qualified corps of
young professionals.
	   
