<HEADLINE>
Geac, NeuConcept form insurance solution pact, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Geac, NeuConcept form insurance solution pact, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   Rozana SaniASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   GEAC Computers (M) Sdn Bhd is teaming up with NeuConcept
Business Development (M) Sdn Bhd to deliver a turnkey solution for
the local insurance market.
	   Through the partnership, NeuConcept will deliver Geac's
Insurance FastApps which, among others, will help users simplify
annual insurance regulatory reporting requirements and provide
rapid general ledger system deployment for Year 2000 (Y2K)
compliance.
	   Geac's country manager Lana Chan said the combined SmartStream
Ledger and SmartStream Decision Support client-server applications
within Insurance FastApps will provide cost-effective and
dependable results in a mission-critical environment.
	   ``We are targeting to provide a `pre-packaged' solution that is
low in cost and able to give fast returns on investment. This was
previously not available as insurance companies needed to go to
consultancy houses and painfully develop such solutions from
scratch,'' Chan said at the Geac and NeuConcept's joint Press
announcement in Petaling Jaya last week.
	   NeuConcept's senior consultant G.S. Teo said he was optimistic
about the market's acceptance on the product.
	   ``Insurance FastApps not only allows companies to use data
derived from existing systems, it also takes on independent
functions that allow the companies' main systems to run its daily
operations. As it helps prioritise functions, Insurance FastApps is
the key for companies pursuing ISO 9000 certification,'' he said.
	   For companies needing to move their financial applications from
a mainframe to a client-server infrastructure to handle Y2K
compliance, Insurance FastApps can do so without chart of accounts
changes or vendor or customer master file coding, he added.
	   Teo said the solution is especially suitable for insurance
companies whose annual turnover are in the range of RM100 million
to RM150 million, and constitute some 40 per cent of the market.
``With a start-up price of RM250,000, we are confident of closing
at least four deals by year-end for Insurance Fast-Apps,'' he said.
	   According to Teo, the implementation period for Insurance
FastApps could span from three to six months before going live.
	   The solution runs on IBM's reduced instruction set computer
(RISC) and NT servers with either Sybase or Microsoft SQL Server
database.
	   As the turnkey solution uses the IBM platforms, NeuConcept has
struck up a partnership with IBM RS/6000 and personal system group
products distributor Azure Technologies (M) Sdn Bhd to deliver a
total solution.
	   
</TEXT>
