	   SEREMBAN, Sun. - State DAP chairman Wong Zee Nyok said members
in the State respected the decision to suspend national
vice-chairman Liew Ah Kim and treasurer Fung Ket Wing, and remove
national publicity secretary Wee Choo Keong from his post.
	   He said members believed the move by the Central Executive
Committee was in the party's interest and were confident the
decision was taken only after having considered all consequences.
	   ``Every political party in the country has its share of problems
and we must respect any decision by our party leaders in the faith
that it is for the good of the party,'' he said.
	   He said all programmes and activities organised by the State
party would continue as scheduled and that there were no grievances
among State party members with regard to the decision.
	   
