<HEADLINE>
BCDA to Develop Another Housing Community In Tagig, BUSINESS DAILY
</HEADLINE>
BCDA to Develop Another Housing Community In Tagig, BUSINESS DAILY &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   BUSINESS DAILY
   PHILIPPINES
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   The Bases Conversion Development Authority (BCDA) will develop
another housing community in Tagig for members of Sprinxville
Neighborhood Association Inc. (SNAI) on a 4.3-hectare portion of
the eight-hectare land allocated for the former residents of Fort
Bonifacio.
	   In a memorandum of agreement (MOA) signed recently between BCDA
and SNAI, BCDA will provide electricity, potable water supply,
road, networks, drainage system and an access road that would link
it to the C-5 Road.
	   The new housing site is located on a prime land near the two
major housing communities -- Centennial Village and Diego Silang --
along the C-5 Road in Taguig.
	   The project is part of BCDA's ongoing shelter program under the
Ramos administration as a commitment to provide affordable and
decent housing units to members of the Armed Forces of the
Philippines (AFP) and the Philippine National Police (PNP).
	   BCDA, through the Public Estates Authority (PEA), would pay the
qualified member-beneficiaries of SNAI of the assessed value of
their temporary structure at Fort Bonifacio but not to exceed
P500,000 net of tax and the cost of land in two installments.
	   The firsts installment will be 70% of the amount to be released
immediately when the relocation site has been developed or ready
for housing construction. The remaining 30% will be released
immediately upon vacating their present structures.
	   BCDA will sell the developed lots to qualified SNAI
member-beneficiaries.
	   The total area will be determined based on the homelots each
member-beneficiary is entitled in accordance with the BCDA-approved
guidelines as follows: 36 square meters (sq.m.) for owners of
structures valued up to P100,000; 60 sq.m. for owners of structures
valued above P100,000 up to P300,000; and 72 sq.m. for owner of
structures valued above P300,000.
	   SNAI will pay the cost of home at a subsidized rate of P500 per
square meter through automatic deductions from the payment of the
structures of member-beneficiaries.
	   
</TEXT>
