AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Aspen Tower, the first resort condominium tower in Alabang, has
reached its last floor of construction. The residential development
is a 23-storey tower and is the first of the four luxurious
buildings of Parkway Place Resort Towers in Filinvest Corporate
City (FCC) in Alabang, Muntinlupa.
	   Sales have been brisk, with around 80% of the units already
sold. Some of the units will be ready for turnover by yearend.
	   Parkway Place Resort Towers offer resort living features. It has
a 25-meter swimming pool with in-water lounge, lush tropical
foliage, and a breathtaking view of Manila Bay, Laguna Lake, and
the future Water Gardens -- a landscaped natural creek weaving
through FCC inspired by the famed San Antonio River Walk.
	   Parkway Place's wide variety of amenities include a gym, sauna,
jacuzzi, multi-purpose cabana, day-care center, kiddie pool and
playground.
	   Furthermore, among its first-class features are a porte cochere
entry, a private lift with a spectacular view, and a chain of
retail shops.
	   Future residents of Aspen Tower will find convenience in
shopping with the recently opened Festival SuperMall which is right
across the luxurious residential complex. The model units of
Parkway Place are open for viewing daily. They are located near the
FCC Marketing Office and Exhibit Center along Corporate Avenue.
	   
