<HEADLINE>
Russia promises new ideas for nuclear meeting
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Russia will bring news ideas to a meeting in
London called to discuss recent nuclear tests in India and
Pakistan, a Foreign Ministry spokesman said Tuesday.
	   The ITAR-Tass news agency, which reported the comments by
spokesman Vladimir Rakhmanin, did not elaborate.
	   Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov is scheduled to attend
the meeting Friday with other representatives of the Group of
Eight.
	   British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook has said the meeting will
coordinate the position of the eight countries toward the new
nuclear powers.
