<HEADLINE>
Kedah: No contest for top two posts, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Kedah: No contest for top two posts, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   ALOR STAR, Sun. - The Kedah Umno liaison committee decided
unanimously last night to ask all divisions in the State to ensure
there is no contest for the president's and deputy president's
posts in next year's party elections.
	   State Umno liaison chief Tan Sri Sanusi Junid said the committee
decided that Datuk Seri Dr Mahathir Mohamad and Datuk Seri Anwar
Ibrahim should not be challenged to enable them to concentrate on
overcoming the nation's economic problems.
	   ``We will ask all divisions in Kedah to propose the posts are
not contested,'' he told a Press conference today.
	   Sanusi said the divisional chiefs agreed time and efforts should
be spent on solving the economic problems.
	   Asked why the committee had made such a decision now when the
party elections were only next year, he said: ``Because we found
that some campaigning has started.
	   ``If the campaign continues, we will not be able to focus on
other important matters.''
	   
</TEXT>
