<HEADLINE>
Johor Umno convention begins today, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Johor Umno convention begins today, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   JOHOR BARU, Sun.- The third Johor Umno Convention will be held
over two days from tomorrow in Sibu Island, off Mersing.
	   The convention, to be held at the Johor Corporation-owned Pulau
Sibu Island Resort, will be officially opened by deputy Umno
president Datuk Seri Anwar Ibrahim.
	   Some 350 delegates from the 20 Johor Umno divisions will attend
the convention which will have the theme `National Economic Agenda:
Reformation, Social Justice and Balanced Development'.
	   Menteri Besar Datuk Abdul Ghani Othman, who is also Johor Umno
chief, will deliver a keynote address.
	   Meanwhile Anwar, who is also Deputy Prime Minister, in his
foreword in the convention souvenir magazine, stressed the need to
rid nepotism, corruption and crony capitalism in Umno based on its
founding principles and to strengthen the party.
	   He said Umno should not only continue to protect the interests
of the people, but also strive to achieve social justice.
	   Ghani, in his message, called for solid and responsible leaders
to bring the party to greater heights, adding they should be
sincere, fair and balanced for the benefit of the people.
	   He said Umno should also stress on spiritual and social
development and a strong family institution.
	   
</TEXT>
