<HEADLINE>
Growing demand for knowledge workers for the MSC, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Growing demand for knowledge workers for the MSC, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   MULTIMEDIA Development Corporation Sdn Bhd (MDC), the one-stop
agency for the Multimedia Super Corridor project, plans to create
an ``MSC virtual degree'' that will allow students to study various
components of a degree via the electronic media.
	   Its executive chairman Tan Sri Dr Othman Yeop Abdullah said the
effort will go a long way towards creating a Web of potential
knowledge workers spanning the globe.
	   ``We hope that many of these knowledge workers will eventually
make their homes in the MSC,'' he said at a briefing last week.
	   According to Othman, the initiative is part of the Government's
long- term plan to create an adequate skilled workforce for the MSC
which requires about 17,000 knowledge workers over the next five
years.
	   He said besides giving MSC-status companies the flexibility to
recruit knowledge workers from abroad, the Government also aims to
develop local skills for the MSC.
	   Towards this end, Othman said the group enrolment ratio in
tertiary educational institutions would be raised from the current
13 per cent to 20 per cent by the year 2000.
	   ``The higher educational policy has been adjusted to encourage
the growth of private education, and we will see the total number
of universities doubling by the year 2000 with new private
universities set up,'' he said, adding that the Government has
extended benefits under the MSC Bill of Guarantees to qualifying
institutions of higher education.
	   
</TEXT>
