<SLUG> CALL-TO-CONTRIBUTE-DATUK sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Call to contribute to Datuk Johan Ariff fund, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Call to contribute to Datuk Johan Ariff fund, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KOTA BARU, Sun. - Entrepreneur Development Minister Datuk
Mustapa Mohamed has called on former students of Sultan Ismail
College to contribute to the Datuk Johan Ariff education fund.
	   He said the fund, incepted early this year to provide financial
aid to deserving students studying at the school, only managed to
collect RM13,200.
	   ``I am not satisfied with the amount collected so far as the
number of former students is large,'' he said at the scholarship
presentation at the school recently.
	   The fund is in recognition of the late Ray Hall, the school's
former English teacher who contributed significantly to the
development of education particularly in the improvement of the
English language among Kelantan students.
	   Hall, an Irishman who embraced Islam and took the name Johan
Ariff, had played a tremendous role in spuring the college students
to achieve academic excellence during his 15-year teaching career
at the school.
	   Mustapa, who studied under Johan Ariff between 1968 and 1969,
said the fund sponsorship committee had been formed to organise
events to raise more money for the fund.
	   ``We intend to award the scholarship to four deserving students
each year,'' said Mustapa, who is also the committee chairman.
	   Mohd Azmi Ariffin and Nik Suzairin Nik Zahib, both Form Four
students, received the scholarship from Mustapa at the ceremony.
	   
</TEXT>
