<HEADLINE>
89 ex-PSD scholars face bankruptcy action, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
89 ex-PSD scholars face bankruptcy action, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KUANTAN, Sun. - The Public Service Department is taking
bankruptcy action against 89 students, whom it sponsored, for
breaking the terms of their contract, Deputy Minister in the Prime
Minister's Department Datuk Fauzi Abdul Rahman said today.
	   He said the bankruptcy action was the last resort as they had
repeatedly ignored warnings.
	   Fauzi said PSD-sponsored students not undertaking professional
courses were required to work in the public sector for two to five
years. It would be four to 10 years for those taking professional
courses.
	   In default, PSD had to be paid between RM35,000 and RM90,000 for
those who studied in a local university, and RM67,000 to RM160,000
for students who went abroad.
	   Overall, action has been taken against 1,500 PSD scholarship
holders.
	   Fauzi was speaking to reporters after officiating at the
district Hawkers Day.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES all rights
reserved as distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
