<HEADLINE>

</HEADLINE>
BULLETIN-IMMEDIATE BROADCAST REQUESTED
URBAN AND SMALL STREAM FLOOD ADVISORY
NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE SAN JUAN PR


...THE NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE IN SAN JUAN PR HAS ISSUED AN URBAN
AND SMALL STREAM FLOOD ADVISORY EFFECTIVE UNTIL 330 PM AST FOR THE
MUNICIPALITIES OF MARICAO...LAS MARIAS...MAYAGUEZ AND HORMIGUEROS...

...NUMEROUS SHOWERS AND ISOLATED THUNDERSTORMS...SOME WITH HEAVY
RAINFALL WERE OCCURRING ACROSS THE INTERIOR AND WEST SECTIONS OF
PUERTO RICO. DOPPLER RADAR ESTIMATES INDICATED UP TO TWO
INCHES OF RAIN IN SEVERAL PLACES ACROSS THE ADVISORY AREA AND
A SKYWARN OBSERVER FROM MAYAGUEZ INDICATED SEVERAL STREETS AND
LOW LYING AREAS FLOODED IN MAYAGUEZ. ALTHOUGH THESE SHOWERS AND
STORMS WERE MOVING RAPIDLY WEST...AN ADDITIONAL INCH OR TWO OF
RAINFALL CAN BE EXPECTED THROUGH 330 PM.

MOTORISTS AND PEDESTRIANS IN OR PASSING THROUGH THE ADVISORY AREA
THIS AFTERNOON SHOULD AVOID CROSSING FLOODED ROADS...AND
ALLOW EXTRA TIME TO REACH THEIR DESTINATIONS. REMEMBER...CARS CAN
EASILY STALL IN THE WATER AND BE CARRIED AWAY IN ANY CURRENT.
PEDESTRIANS ARE ALSO ADVISED TO STAY AWAY FROM RISING CREEKS.

IF YOUR VEHICLE STALLS...ABANDON IT IMMEDIATELY AND SEEK HIGHER
GROUND. BE ESPECIALLY CAUTIOUS WHEN APPROACHING BRIDGES AND DIPS IN
THE ROAD. MANY DEATHS HAVE BEEN CAUSED BY ATTEMPTS TO MOVE STALLED
VEHICLES.

DO NOT ATTEMPT TO CROSS A FLOWING STREAM ON FOOT WHERE WATER IS ABOVE
YOUR KNEES.
