<HEADLINE>
Two held in cough mixture seizure, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Two held in cough mixture seizure, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   TANAH MERAH, Sun. - Police arrested two people in connection
with the seizure of 68 litres of cough mixture during a raid at a
house near Taman Sinaran, two days ago.
	   A police party picked up the men, aged 30 and 33, in a 2am raid.
	   Tanah Merah police chief Deputy Superintendent Roslan Ahmad said
today that one of them was wanted by police to assist in
investigations into illegal distribution of cough mixture in the
State.
	   He added that the cough mixture was believed to have been
brought in from other States for distribution in the district.
	   Roslan added that the men would be charged under Section 12(2)
of the Dangerous Drugs Act 1986.
	   
</TEXT>
