<HEADLINE>
Riots impair Surakarta business, JAKARTA POST
</HEADLINE>
Riots impair Surakarta business, JAKARTA POST &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   JAKARTA POST
   INDONESIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   SURAKARTA, Central Java: Material damages in Surakarta from the
two days of widespread unrest on May 14 and May 15 are estimated to
total Rp 457.5 billion.
	   Rahmadi Wahyudi, head of the team assessing the damage, said
much of the losses were from the 10 shopping plazas and 23
showrooms torched during the riots.
	   The damage to shopping plazas, showrooms and major supermarkets
alone are estimated at Rp 189.6 billion.
	   Another 58 individual shops and 14 factories were also burned in
the anarchy, while dozens of other buildings were severely damaged.
	   ``The material damages are very high, but the greater loss comes
from the trauma of the riots which might affect the business
climate in Surakarta,'' Rahmadi said here yesterday.
	   He feared businesspeople might be less inclined to invest here
in the future, causing commercial activity in Surakarta to come to
a complete standstill.
	   ``The security apparatus must provide assurances that the city
is again safe for business so any fears which may be lingering can
be dispelled,'' he said. 
</TEXT>
