<SLUG> BC-Sports-Tennis-DFS Classic, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Rain holds up women's Wimbledon warm-up
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: Adds quotes Stubbs in 5th graf, updates result

<TEXT>
	   BIRMINGHAM, England (AP) _ Rain disrupted the DFS Classic for
the second straight day Tuesday, but Steffi Graf did manage to get
in some practice for her latest comeback.
	   Graf, who has played in only two tournaments since undergoing
knee surgery last year, is looking for as much match play as
possible before Wimbledon.
	   Seeded No. 1 here, the German is scheduled to play Australian
qualifier Rennae Stubbs in a second-round match Wednesday.
	   Stubbs, who is coming back from eight months out with a wrist
injury, said she would be nervous playing the former World number
one.
	   ``It'll be a big occasion and there will be a lot of interest in
Steffi coming back _ but I hope we'll have some fun,'' Stubbs said
after beating Shi-Ting Wang of Chinese Taipei in a first round
match Tuesday.
	   ``I've practised a lot against her, so I'm used to running
around picking up the balls and giving her lots of confidence. I
really hope she makes a successful comeback but I hope she's not
too successful just yet.''
	   Italy's Laura Golarsa, a quarter-finalist at Wimbledon in 1989,
won the first completed match of the grass-court tournament
Tuesday.
	   Her match against Czech Denisa Chladkova was delayed by three
hours, and then again for almost an hour during the second set, but
the rain stopped long enough for Golarsa, ranked 79th in the world,
to win 6-3, 7-5.
	   (str/jp)	   
</TEXT>
