spelling of Ketola's first name &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   BOLOGNA, Italy (AP) - Down 3-0 in the last set and facing
elimination, top seed Alberto Berasategui withdrew in the first
round of the 340,000 Carisbo international tournament Tuesday.
	   Berasategui of Spain, the 1996 winner here, was losing to Hernan
Gumy of Argentina 5-7, 7-6 (4), 3-0 when he retired with a thigh
muscle cramp from the dlrs 340,000 clay court event.
	   Gumy now faces Juan Antonio Marin of Costa Rica, who defeated
Tuomas Ketola of Finland 6-4, 7-6 (3) Tuesday.
	   In first-round other matches, third-seed Julian Alonso overcame
fellow Spaniard Pepe Imaz 6-4, 6-4, sixth-seed Karim Alami of
Morocco defeated Spain's David Sanchez, 6-4, 6-2 and eighth-seed
Dominik Hrbaty of Slovakia out-muscled Javier Sanchez, also of
Spain, 6-4, 4-6, 6-3.
