<HEADLINE>
What's Cooking?, BUSINESS DAILY
</HEADLINE>
What's Cooking?, BUSINESS DAILY &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   BUSINESS DAILY
   PHILIPPINES
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Winners Restaurant. Founded on the elements of inspiration,
faith in people, and old-fashioned values, this new restaurant
along Arnaiz Ave.
	   (Pasay Road) is the brainchild of the young and dynamic
entrepreneurs from new company World's Best Food International. The
group has come up with the first thematic restaurant in honor the
world's greatest achievers.
	   Unlike other themed restaurants, Winners goes beyond coordinated
decor. It highlights world-class greats like bowling wunderkind
Paeng Nepomuceno, pool wizard Efren ``Bata'' Reyes, and golf
prodigy Tiger Woods. Winners restaurant also celebrates Lea
Salonga's broadway triumph, the victorious EDSA Revolution, and
Nelson Mandela's movement in South Africa.
	   The Winners menu specializes in Fusion Cuisine. It mixes
influences of Hispanic, Californian, Continental, and Filipino
culinary cultures. The list of entrees include New Zealand Mussels
Baked in Butter, Crispy Fried Mongo and Shrimps Wrapped in Sweet
Potato Chips, Broiled Eggplant Soup Garnished with Pork Crackling,
and Fresh Pasta Stuffed with Cheese and Smothered in Meaty Sauce.
	   TRATTORIA GOURMET'S. An innovative restaurant idea
conceptualized a year and a half ago by entrepreneurs Paolo Nesi of
L'Opera Restaurant and Ernest Escaler of the Gourmet's Cafe group,
Trattoria Gourmet's has opened another branch at the ground level
of Robinson's Place in Ermita. The cozy, attractive restaurant
combines the best of both L'Opera and Gourmet's Cafe, achieved
through a healthful, authentic Italian menu. Crisp-crusted pizzas,
organically grown salad greens, fresh pasta, and a delectable
selection of entrees done in the light Mediterranean fashion are
offered daily. A new addition is its coffee and grappa bar
featuring the popular Gourmet Coffee and a choice selection of
plain and flavored grappas. This pleasant addition to the
reinvigorated Ermita-Malate scene promises to be a pleasant stop
for both the dining and late night crowds.
	   MARIO'S. Sumptuous ``Breakfast Buffet,'' featuring a wide
assortment of breakfast delights, is offered every Tuesday and
Thursday at Mario's Ayala (P195++) and Ortigas (P255++). Both
branches also offer ``Dine and Wine on Us,'' which features beef
dishes that may come with a complimentary glass or bottle of house
wine; and ``Lunch Smorgasbord'' for only P245++ (Monday-Saturday at
Ortigas; until Friday at Ayala). The Mario's Quezon City outlet,
meanwhile, serves the affordable ``Executive Lunch Express,''
	   featuring the chef's special with soup and dessert, during
weekdays.
	   Mario's also offers the ``Early Bird Promo,'' which gives
discounts of 20% on food and beverages from 5-7 p.m. Try the
restaurant's Truly Fruities, thirst-quenching fresh fruit juices,
as well as its revved up function rooms, for both business and
pleasure.
	   BENNIGAN's. From its interesting menu, Bennigan's in Glorietta,
Makati unveils Shrimp Fan-tastic. One serving consists of five
jumbo tempura shrimps, garnished with a lemon wedge, a scoop of
cole slaw, seasoned french fries, Jalapeno tartar sauce, and
cocktail sauce.
	   BEVERLY HILLS DELI. At its Boni branch, lunchtime is ``All You
Can Eat''
	   time, every weekday, for only P195++. At the Boni and Greenbelt
Delis, unique burger selections with thick, oven-roasted fries are
also offered.
	   Affordable ``Dinner Sizzlers'' with free bottomless softdrinks
are available in all Delis.
	   STUDEBAKER'S. The Top Down presents ``Wall Street Lunch,''
featuring small board lunch variations: salad buffet of choice
fillings and dressings (P100++); pasta buffet corner featuring
pasta prepared according to a customer's preference (P130++); and
chef's special - main courses of beef, pork, fish, and fowl
(P160++). Also included in the food promo: par value lunch: salad
and pasta bar only (P160++); big board lunch: salad, pasta, and
chef's special (P250++).
	   Kenny Rogers Roasters. Serving more than just its trademark
roasted chicken, Kenny Rogers introduces its latest sure winner:
Honey Bourbon Baby Back Ribs. Coming from the leanest back portion
of suckling pigs, the baby back is baked until tender - the meat
practically falls off the bone.
	   Selecta Collection. In line with the Centennial celebration,
Selecta Dairy Products Inc. celebrates the uniqueness of Filipino
taste with the Selecta Collection Flavors of the Islands featuring
favorite specialties from different parts of country, namely, Cebu
Mangga Espesyal, Bohol Ube Leche Flan, Batangas Tsokolate at Kasuy,
Laguna Buco Pandan Cake, and Quezon Coco Fiesta.
	   The attractive can designs for the new Selecta collection is
designed by noted cartoonist Larry Alcala. They are hinged on
Alcala's whimsical portrayal of the average Filipino. The cans
exhibit famous landmarks in history and, as always, Alcala's
self-caricature is hidden in the picture.
	   Alcala admits having to do some brushing up on his History. He
also had to gather photographs of historical places and monuments,
choose which to feature, and chronologically fit them into a
lay-out that would create a good design.
	   photo captions: 1. Winners Manager Reginald Miniano and Chef
Gillete Garcia with some of the restaurant's winning specialties.
	   2. Kenny Rogers' Honey Bourbon Baby Back Ribs.
	   3. Trattoria Gourmet's country-style setting.
	   4. Bennigan's Shrimp Fan-tastic.
	   5. Selecta's Ube Leche Flan Flavor of the Islands.
	   6. Cartoonist Alcala, with Selecta officials, showing his
designs for the Flavors of the Islands ice cream cans.
	   
