<SLUG> BC-Russia-Japanese Photos </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Photos by Japanese leader to be displayed in Moscow museum
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Photographs taken by Japanese Prime Minister
Ryutaro Hashimoto will be displayed at the Tretyakov Art Gallery in
Moscow, a news agency reported Tuesday.
	   Hashimoto's wife, Kumiko, will open the display on Thursday,
ITAR-Tass said, quoting the Japanese Embassy.
	   Japanese Ambassador Takehiro Togo said the photographs show
Japanese landscapes, sights in other countries and three
photographs taken by the prime minister during a meeting with
Russian President Boris Yeltsin in the Siberian city of
Krasnoyarsk.
	   The ambassador said Hashimoto has long been interested in
photography and has had other personal exhibitions in San Francisco
and Singapore.
	   The exhibition will also include old Japanese photographs,
ITAR-Tass said.
	   Mrs. Hashimoto will be in Russia at the invitation of Yeltsin's
wife, Naina.
	   (ls) 	   
</TEXT>
