	   Outback's Kiddie Adventure. It was a fun-filled afternoon of
prizes and surprises when Outback Steakhouse treated some of the
members of Solid Bank's Fun Saver's Club to an afternoon of Aussie
adventure. The kids participated in activities hosted by Outback's
staff which included a tour of the restaurant, coloring activities,
and sampling some of the dishes in Outback's Joey Menu. Outback
Steakhouse is located at the second level of Robinson's Place
Manila.
	   'Madrasta' Stars Grace HBO's Show Party. Young stars Patrick
Garcia and Camille Pratts and film director Olivia Lamasan of the
critically-acclaimed and top-grossing Filipino film Madrasta graced
HBO's Cable Show Party held recently at the Conservatory of The
Peninsula Manila. Madrasta, a film scripted by noted screenwriter
Ricky Lee and topbilled by star actress Sharon Cuneta (Cuneta's
performance in this movie won for her all major acting awards last
year) was shown on Cinemax last month as part of its Asian Film
Festival package. Seen partying with the cast were HBO officials
Jacelyn Kek, sales manager; Suarina Chua, director affiliate sales;
Jim Marturano, SVP-sales and marketing; Dan Murell, managing
director; Mack Perryman, SVP-programming and promotions; and
Caroline Wong, marketing manager.
	   Teaching through TV. The National Commission for Culture and the
Arts (NCAA) and Arkipelago Productions have teamed up to produce a
weekly prime time television show for kids.
	   Arkipelago Productions received a P300,000 grant to partially
defray the expenses in the production of Likha, a three-month
tele-magazine that will feature the unique folk art culture of
Quezon province. The NCAA gave the grant to encourage the
development of local productions and the documentation and
promotion of indigenous cultural heritage.
	   The brainchild of playwright and Arkipelago Executive Director
Malu Maniquiz, Likha will be telecast on CBS Channel 8, the Quezon
provincial channel with broadcast reaching up to Marinduque,
Oriental and Occidental Mindoro, Batangas, and parts of Bicol and
Laguna.
	   Initially, the show will focus on Mt. Banahaw and the
communities and towns at the foot of the mountain, particularly
Lucban, Tayabas, Sariaya, Candelaria, Dolores, and Tiaong.
According to Maniquiz, the impact of the show in providing
alternative local programming in Southern Tagalog will encourage
the community to value their culture more and help them develop
positive Filipino values.
	   Side A's Successful Concert. Pop band Side A performed to an
overflowing crowd of enthusiastic partygoers at the Concert Park of
Island Cove Resort &AMP; Leisure Park in Binakayan, Kawit, Cavite last
May 1. The show was part of a special summer presentation sponsored
by 109.9 Cross Over, Coca-Cola Bottler Phils., Dunkin Donuts
Cavite, Le Brumisateur Evian, Australian Wines, Denman, Emperor
Pizza Bakeshop and Restaurant, LA Looks Styling Gel, Loida's
Garden, Purefoods Tender Juicy Hotdog, Sharp Phils. Corp., V.
	   Santera Sash and Factory &AMP; Steel Works and AV World Corp.
	   
</TEXT>
