<HEADLINE>
Rains force evacuations in southern Russia
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Heavy rains caused a river in southern Russia to
flood, forcing the evacuation of 1,200 people from a town in the
Stavropol region, a news agency said Tuesday.
	   One-meter (Three-feet) deep water from the Sukhaya Buivola River
flooded one-story buildings in Blagodarny, the news agency said.
	   Heavy rains also hit the adjoining Ipatovo district, flooding
200 homes and damaging an electricity sub-station, it said.
	   Weather officials say more than 10 centimeters (nearly 4 inches)
of rain fell on the Blagodarny and Ipatovo districts in 3-1/2
hours. That's the usual rainfall for two months.
