<HEADLINE>
Report: 32 Arabs arrested for smuggling weapons from Jordan
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   JERUSALEM (AP) _ Thirty-two Arabs have been arrested on
suspicion of smuggling weapons including machine guns and assault
rifles into Israel from Jordan, police said.
	   Police spokeswoman Linda Menuhin said a publication ban on the
arrests had been lifted Tuesday but she could not specify when the
arrests had been carried out. She had no further details on the
suspects.
	   Israel radio reported that the suspects included Palestinians
from the West Bank and Arab citizens of Israel.
	   Uzi submachine guns, assault rifles and hand guns were smuggled
by the suspects into Israel through the northern Naharayim border
crossing with Jordan, Israel radio reported.
	   The report said eight suspects will remain in custody until the
end of their trials and that charges against some of the group may
include intention to harm the state.
	   In February, the Israeli military intercepted a bid to smuggle
two boatloads of weapons and arms from Jordan via the Dead Sea.
