<HEADLINE>
Ratings for Affin bonds stay, BUSINESS TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Ratings for Affin bonds stay, BUSINESS TIMES &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   BUSINESS TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   AFFIN Holdings Bhd's RM225 million and RM240 million guaranteed
redeemable bond issues have been reviewed and maintained at AA1(bg)
and AAA(bg) ratings respectively by Rating Agency Malaysia Bhd
(RAM). The ratings reflect the strength of the bank guarantee
provided by Public Bank Bhd and Malayan Banking Bhd which enhanced
the credit risk profile of both debt securities issued beyond that
of the issuing company's inherent or stand- alone risk.
Furthermore, RAM said, all risks associated with the debt
facilities are expected to be absorbed by the guarantors. The
rating agency pointed out that it last rated Public Bank at AA1
while Malayan Banking carries a AAA rating.
	   
</TEXT>
