<HEADLINE>
Spice Girls share stage with Pavarotti in Italy
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with concert beginning, details; trims at end &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   MODENA, Italy (AP) _ It was a taste of Pavarotti both spicey and
spiked, with a touch of soul.
	   The tenor of his times sang in an outdoor song-fest Tuesday
night directed by Spike Lee and co-starring pop performers like the
Spice Girls, Stevie Wonder and Jon Bon Jovi.
	   The Ginger-less Spice group were giving their first performance
since their split with ``Ginger Spice,'' Geri Halliwell, was
announced.
	   The four and Pavarotti joined forces on the program for the song
``Viva Forever.''
	   Proceeds of the fifth annual ``Pavarotti and Friends'' charity
concert were destined to help poor children in the African nation
of Liberia. The show in a park in this northern city was broadcast
live on Italy's flagship state television channel, RAI-1.
	   A chorus of Liberian children opened the concert. Model Naomi
Campbell and designer Donatella Versace made surprise appearances,
appealing for contributions for the cause.
	   Also appearing was Celine Dion, performing a song associated
with a large ship. Pavarotti did not appear, but many in the
audience sang along with the theme from ``Titanic.''
	   As the 62-year-old Pavarotti has been making fewer opera
appearances in recent years, his pop career is on the upswing.
	   Other performers on the program were Vanessa Williams, Natalie
Cole, Trisha Yearwood and Italian stars Eros Ramazzotti, Zucchero
and Pino Daniele.
	   (djw)
</TEXT>
