<HEADLINE>
Guide to help realise dreams, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Guide to help realise dreams, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   Prasanna RamanASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   AS the title goes, this book is meant to help people win. Shiv
Khera, the author, is a sought-after and well-known speaker,
motivator and entrepreneur based in the United States.
	   Khera describes his book as a construction manual, a cookbook,
and a guidebook.
	   As a construction manual, it is said to describe tools that
readers need for success and offers blueprints to build a
successful and rewarding life.
	   As a cookbook, it lists the ingredients, or the principles that
readers need to follow to become successful and the recipe for
mixing them in the correct proportions.
	   And as a guidebook, the book provides a step-by-step how-to book
that will take readers from dreaming about success to unlocking
one's potential for success.
	   The book looks simple but the author does not encourage the book
to be completed in one reading because the concepts cannot be
absorbed by either casual or hurried reading.
	   ``It should be read slowly and carefully, one chapter at a time.
Don't move on to the next chapter until you are sure you understand
every concept in the previous chapter,'' Khera stressed in his
preface.
	   Eight chapters make up this book. Chapter one is on the
Importance of Attitude - Building a Positive Attitude and this is
followed by Success - Winning Strategies.
	   Chapter three is on Motivation - Motivating Yourself and Others
Every Day. The next chapter focuses on building positive
self-esteem and image, followed by chapter five which is basically
on interpersonal skills, helping the reader to build a pleasing
personality.
	   Forming positive habits and character is covered in chapter six,
while the next chapter is devoted to helping the reader to set and
achieve goals. The final chapter is on Values and Vision, stressing
on doing the right thing for the right reason.
	   Here's a good book to read especially in these times when many
feel that they are unable to achieve their dreams.
	   
</TEXT>
