MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   THREE-month KLibor futures on the Malaysia Monetary Exchange
(MME) ended lower yesterday as interbank rates firmed up.
	   Three-month underlying Kuala Lumpur Interbank Offered Rates
(KLibor) increased to 11.04 per cent from 11.02 per cent
previously, following intervention by Bank Negara Malaysia.
	   Only three contract months were traded yesterday with a total
volume of 16 lots.
	   September 98 was down by seven ticks to 88.93 with five lots
traded, December 98 dropped by seven ticks to 88.93 with six lots
changing hands, while March 99 declined by one tick to 88.92 with
five lots traded.
	   Mr Chris Podbury of JF Apex Futures said trading in the futures
market was listless in quiet tone yesterday.
	   ``We, however, expect the three-month KLibor futures to continue
to trade sideways to higher in the near term,'' he added.
	   
