	   RINGGIT closed slightly lower against the US dollar yesterday on
weak fundamentals in the market, dealers said.
	   The local unit ended at 3.9950/005 to the greenback as against
3.9700/900 last Friday.
	   Dealers attributed the ringgit's easier sentiment as well as
other regional currencies to the weakening yen.
	   The local unit was, however, higher against the Singapore dollar
at 2.3331/335 from 2.3422/582, stronger against the yen at
2.8395/840 from 2.8477/641 but declined against the Deutschemark to
2.2475/255 from 2.2423/542 and fell against pound sterling to
6.5190/539 from 6.5037/404 last Friday.
	   
