Russian foreign minister to visit Lithuania
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov will
visit Lithuania on Saturday, a spokesman said.
	   Primakov will have talks with Lithuanian Foreign Minister
Algirdas Saudargas and meet President Valdas Adamkus and Prime
Minister Gediminas Vagnorius.
	   The two former Soviet republics will discuss bilateral
cooperation and regional security issues, Foreign Ministry Vladimir
Rakhmanin said at a briefing, according to the ITAR-Tass news
agency.
