<HEADLINE>
Tin, BUSINESS TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Tin, BUSINESS TIMES &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   BUSINESS TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   THE price on the Kuala Lumpur Tin Market rose 33 sen to RM23.53
per kg following the weakening of the ringgit against the US
dollar, dealers said.
	   The rise yesterday was an adjustment following the weakening of
the ringgit, they said, pointing out that last Friday tin on the
London Metal Exchnage dropped US$20 and that this meant there was
no adverse impact from that market here.
	   The ringgit breached the 4.00 level against the US dollar
yesterday. At 12.23pm, the ringgit stood at 4.0050 after sliding to
as low as 4.0300.
	   Buying on the KLTM yesterday came mainly from European and local
buyers.
	   At the opening level, buyers made bids for 148 tonnes while
sellers offered to sell 104 tonnes. Turnover declined to 104 tonnes
from 140 tonnes last Friday.
	   The premium commanded by the KLTM over the LME stood at US$55
from US$24 at the end of last week.
	   
</TEXT>
