	   KOTA BARU, Sun. - Fourteen vehicles were destroyed when a fire
razed a motor workshop at Jalan Long Yunus yesterday.
	   An adjacent shophouse was also destroyed in the incident which
occurred about 6.15pm.
	   Ten of the vehicles destroyed in the blaze had been left at the
shop for repairs.
	   Workshop proprietor Lin Tong Gan, 27, estimated the loss at
RM500,000.
	   State Fire and Rescue Department director Abdul Aziz Harun said
firemen in three engines spent about 90 minutes to bring the blaze
under control and prevented it from spreading to nearby buildings,
including a double- storey house and a petrol station.
	   Abdul Aziz added that initial investigations revealed the fire
might have started from a gas stove.
	   A motor-cyclist, Abdul Kadir Abdul Rahman, 63, of Kampung
Dendang, who fell off his machine in Ketereh two days ago, died at
the Universiti Sains Malaysia Hospital in Kubang Kerian about
10.10am today. He had head and body injuries.
	   District traffic chief Assistant Superintendent Mohd Sany Ismail
said Abdul Kadir skidded after going over a pothole on Friday.
	   
