	   MALAYSIAN rubber prices closed lower, reflecting weak regional
prices and lack of demand from buyers.
	   A dealer said the market was quiet and this was due to worries
about regional uncertainties.
	   ``Prices in Indonesia, Thailand and Singapore are all bearish.
The local price adjusted itself to regional levels,'' a dealer
said.
