<HEADLINE>
Gopeng to market Australian multimedia course, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Gopeng to market Australian multimedia course, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   GOPENG Bhd has been appointed to market a multimedia course that
is being offered by an Australian university.
	   This followed the signing of an agreement by Gopeng's
subsidiary, Gopeng Technologies Systems Sdn Bhd, with Edith Cowan
University of Australia. It was signed in Kuala Lumpur on Saturday.
	   A third party to this agreement is multimedia firm Prism
(Australia), which had a hand in designing the courses and will
assist in the training of local teachers.
	   So far, Gopeng has finalised an agreement with a local college
which will be conducting the course. The course is expected to
commence this November and 60 students are expected to enrol.
	   Negotiations are ongoing with two other colleges and are
expected to be finalised within two months, said Hamdan.
	   The company declined to reveal the costs of the course.
	   ``The fee structure has not been finalised yet, but will be
comparable with fees of other twinning courses,'' Hamdan said.
	   Edith Cowan University's diploma course in multimedia currently
costs about A$10,800 (RM25,920) per year for overseas students.
	   Gopeng executive chairman Datuk Mohamed Hamdan Hazizi said it is
the group's intention to expand their activities especially in
education.
	   
</TEXT>
