<SLUG> BC-Sports-Track-Bratislava </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Four year's best records set at Slovnaft
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BRATISLAVA, Slovakia (AP) _ Athletes in four events set records
for the year at the Slovnaft Grand Prix track meet on Tuesday.
	   In the Grand Prix women's discus Russia's Natalya Sadova
improved this year's best world result by 0.27 meter, reaching
67.85 meters. The throw secured the gold for Sadova, beating out
Anastasia Kelesidou from Greece by 2.02 meters. World champion
Beatrice Faumine from New Zeland came up short with 65.43.
	   ``It's my personal record, but it came too early ... I'll have
to keep this form,'' said Sadova after the meet. ``Sixty-seven
meters would get me gold at the European Championship in
Budapest.''
	   Other records were achieved in disciplines not included in the
Grand Prix competition.
	   In men's 3,000 steeplechase, Kenya's Joseph Keter became the
fastest athlete this year with 8 minutes, 8.91 seconds.
	   Running 1,500 meters in 4:00.81, Kenya's Jackline Maranga became
this year's fastest woman in the world.
	   Czech Daniela Bartova marked the European record as she defeated
4.51 meters in pole vault.
	   Running the 110-meter hurdles in 13.13 seconds, Mark Crear from
the United States missed this year's best record by just .01
second.
	   (jd/me)	   
</TEXT>
