<HEADLINE>
New Swiss pen brand identity, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
New Swiss pen brand identity, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   CARAN d'Ache of Switzerland, manufacturer of writing instruments
and colour products, has created for itself a new brand identity as
seen in its recent launch of its latest luxury pen collection
called Leman.
	   Established in 1924 and named after a French artist, the Swiss
pen manufacturer has incorporated a new brand identity into its
Leman collection. The new collection, in a break from the brand
identity used by Caran d'Ache since 1974, carries the new ``CdA''
monogram which ``better reflects the notion of a timeless
quality,'' the company said in a statement issued locally by its
sole Malaysian distributor S.A. Desco Marketing Sdn Bhd. The
monogram is in a dark red background and will crown the cap of each
writing equipment produced by Caran d'Ache in the future.
	   The Leman pen, first presented at the International Stationery
Exhibition in Frankfurt, Germany, on Feb 1 this year, comes with a
spring loaded clip and a two-toned, 18-carat gold fountain pen nib
with a rhodium-coated centre.
	   
