	   KLSE Composite Index Futures traded on the Kuala Lumpur Options
and Financial Futures Exchange (KLoffe) tracked the cash market to
close lower yesterday.
	   Players shorted the futures due to the continued slide of the
ringgit against the US dollar, said dealers.
	   The spot month June futures were down 6.5 points to 493 with
2,755 lots.
	   Its high for the day was 500 and a low of 487.8. Open interests
stood at 19,201.
	   July futures lost 7.0 points to 485.5 with 181 lots traded. It
was traded between a high of 492.5 and a low of 480.4 and its open
interests stood at 1,903.
	   The September and December futures were not traded yesterday and
they settled at 499 and 505 respectively.
	   A dealer said it is difficult to see the upside potential for
futures as the cash market had breached the 500-point psychological
level.
	   
