	   MONTREAL (AP) _ An explosion caused by a severed gas line
shattered a shelter for homeless people in Montreal on Tuesday,
killing two people and injuring about 20, authorities said. One
staff member was missing.
	   The explosion sheared off one entire wall of the three-story
stone building, spilling rubble into the street in historic Old
Montreal. Firefighters accompanied by sniffer dogs were searching
through the debris, unsure if the missing employee was trapped
underneath.
	   A fire department official, Alain Michaud, said the two
fatalities were women, but he had no details about them.
