<HEADLINE>
Roondy Trading launches own brands, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Roondy Trading launches own brands, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   ROONDY Trading Co Sdn Bhd is seeking to expand its footwear
export business with the introduction of its own brands - ``Lewre
1908'' and ``Ezstep''.
	   In an interview, managing director Lew Fong Voon said the
company decided to market its own brands after having supplied to
major global brands over the past nine years.
	   Among these global brands are Red or Dead (UK), Buffalo of
London, Mosquitos (France), Kipling (Belgium), Aldo (North
America), Elle, Courreges, Renoma and Hush Puppies.
	   These exports now make up about 60 per cent of the company's
earnings last year, with the rest coming from supplies to local
in-house outfits like Ricci No and Tangs Studio.
	   ``We do not produce the footwear ourselves but work with a group
of people whom we have had partnerships with over the past
decade,'' said Lew at his office in Shah Alam, Selangor.
	   Roondy is mainly involved in the footwear design process and the
wholesale business.
	   ``Many of the international designers come over to work with our
in-house designers. In many instances, we design our own and
present it to our customers, who then adopt our designs.''
	   He added that each customer would usually launch two sets of new
designs every year - Spring and Fall collections - with each design
having up to 100 different variants.
	   For the company's in-house new brands, Lew said the decision to
produce them was prompted by the need to have a balanced earnings
portfolio, due to competition from cheaper suppliers within the
region.
	   ``Our footwear is not the cheapest when compared to those
produced in countries like Vietnam and China. So, we focused on
quality that our customers are willing to pay for.''
	   Eventually, the company expects half its earnings to come from
its own brands, with the rest coming from supplying to other
brandnames.
	   ``We are lucky to have built up strong relationships with our
clients over the years and they are very supportive of our
aspirations to have our own brands as it caters to a slightly
different market from theirs.''
	   The Lewre 1908 brand is pitched at the medium to upper range
customers, while the Ezstep represents the functional footwear,
catering mainly for office usage.
	   ``We already had two other brands which have done quite well
since we launched them a few years ago. Castel Franco is for the
elegant footwear, while Time Capsule is a range of casual footwear
mainly for the younger customer.''
	   Both these brands were previously available only in overseas
outlets, but Lew said all the company's four in-house brands are
now offered at local outlets.
	   
</TEXT>
