	   PRIME Minister Datuk Seri Dr Mahathir Mohamad yesterday
reiterated Malaysia's stand to get the country's trade and economy
away from the fluctuation in the value of the ringgit.
	   Speaking to reporters after visiting the new Kuala Lumpur
International Airport in Sepang, Dr Mahathir said this can be
easily done by conducting trade on a ``barter-type'' system where
the value of goods will not be influenced by fluctuation in the
local currency's exchange rate.
	   ``What we want to do is to get away from the (fluctuation) in
the value of the ringgit and this can be done easily by conducting
trade on a counter-trade basis or through practical bartering,'' he
said.
	   
