	   TOSHIBA Sales and Services Sdn Bhd recently announced the local
availability of its latest video compact disk (VCD) player, the
TVD-860K.
	   Its assistant general manager of marketing department Chay Kim
Hur said the TVD-860K is a powerful VCD player as it incorporates a
specially designed integrated circuit (IC) which can minimise
distortion to produce clearer images and purer sounds. It features
a sleek, silver body with dual-colour switches that allow users to
know the state of the disk.
	   The VCD player, which is priced at RM999, also features a
karaoke program which allows users to select and program songs from
three disks at the same time. Other options are digital echo
effect, duet capability and 15-step key control, a feature that
allows users to sing in their own key.
	   At the product launch, Toshiba Sales and Services' managing
director K.
	   Takagi said the company has acquired 10 per cent market share of
the local VCD player market which is worth RM100 million, and
intends to increase this to 15 per cent by year-end.
	   
</TEXT>
