<HEADLINE>
Thanks for returning my purse, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Thanks for returning my purse, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   Shazana IsmailASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   AFTER having lunch at Restoran Madinah in Lorong Gopeng, Klang,
I forgot to take my purse. One Guna from the restaurant took the
trouble to drive all the way from Klang to my house in Kelana Jaya
to return it.
	   As he had refused any reward for his honesty, I hope to thank
him again through this letter. I also hope this would encourage
others not to forget to be caring and uphold ethics in times of
economic hardship.
	   
</TEXT>
