<HEADLINE>
Frequent power cuts in PJ causing frustration, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Frequent power cuts in PJ causing frustration, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   M. KaurASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   I WISH to express my frustration over the unscheduled and
frequent power cuts experienced in SS21/16 in Petaling Jaya.
	   We have been experiencing power cuts almost every other day over
the last few weeks.
	   On one day, it lasted from 1pm to 3am (14 hours).
	   On another occasion, it was from 10pm to 7am (nine hours).
	   As you can imagine, in this hot weather, the power cuts are
causing a lot of inconvenience, especially for families with young
children.
	   Schoolchildren are also unable to complete their homework.
	   This problem seems to be common in Petaling Jaya, especially in
Damansara Utama.
	   It is disappointing to note that Tenaga Nasional has not come up
with any information on the situation.
	   Although Tenaga staff can be seen repairing the lines, the
frequency of occurrence and the length of time taken to resolve the
problem are not acceptable.
	   One Tenaga worker said they were still assessing the problem and
they believed it was caused by overloading.
	   They suspect that the number of air-conditioners in the area has
increased, therefore increasing the load.
	   What is Tenaga's solution to the problem?
	   Are they going to react to individual problems or are they
looking at the big picture and solving the problem at source?
	   What action are they taking?
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES all rights
reserved as distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
