<HEADLINE>
Man found stabbed to death, knife recovered, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Man found stabbed to death, knife recovered, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   TUMPAT, Mon. - A 40-year old man was found stabbed to death at
his house in Selehong, Kok Pasir early today.
	   Police identified the victim as Kamarulzaman Jusoh, a purchasing
officer at a hotel in Kota Baru.
	   District police chief Superintendent Muhd Fuad Talib said a
police party was sent to the scene following a telephone call from
a resident about 2.35am.
	   ``At the scene, police found Kamarulzaman sprawled on the
verandah with stab wound on his abdomen,'' he added.
	   He added that the police team also found a knife, believed to
have been used by the killer.
	   At least two men could have been involved in the killing,
according to the police. Kamarulzaman was alone in the house at the
time of the crime.
	   His mother, Fatimah Hassan, 64, said that she was asleep at her
house, which was about 30 metres away from her son's place, when
she heard his call.
	   ``It was about 2am. I went to his house and saw him lying in a
pool of blood with a knife in his hand,'' she added Muhd Fuad said
the body has been sent to the Tumpat Hospital for a post- mortem.
	   Police have classified the case as murder. They believe the
motive could be robbery as his wallet was missing.
	   He appealed to members of the public with information to contact
him or Investigation Officer Deputy Superintendent Hamid Sabran at
09-7257222.
	   
</TEXT>
