	   KOTA KINABALU, Mon. - Several areas in the State have had rain
over the last two weeks but the damage caused by five months of
drought remains.
	   Meteorological Department, Sabah branch director Chang Kung Chew
said the rain was not distributed evenly. Some places were still
facing a drought, especially in the coastal areas of the Kudat and
Sandakan divisions.
	   Only the west coast and the interior had heavy rain.
	   He was responding to questions about the heavy rain yesterday
which resulted in flash floods and caused traffic jams in the State
capital.
	   Several housing estates were flooded.
	   He added that the rains began in late May.
	   
