<HEADLINE>
World Cup: English arrive into Rainy Nantes
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LA BOULE, France (AP) _ England's World Cup squad flew into a
rainy Nantes Tuesday night 20 minutes behind schedule after a
friendly match against a local Caen club.
	   Manager Glenn Hoddle, whose players have hit the headlines
because of their drinking habits, would make no comment as he led
his troops into a bus for an 80-kiometer (50-mile) ride to their
base camp at the Hotel du Golf International near the seaside
resort of La Boule.
	   The squad was scheduled to have a training session at Stade
Moreau Defarge Wednesday afternoon.
	   Tuesday's warm-up match in Caens was held behind closed doors
and the only news to filter through was that England won 1-0 with
an 85th minute goal from Paul Scholes.
