<SLUG> BC-Spain-Arafat </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Arafat maintains need for guns to defend Mideast peace process
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MADRID, Spain (AP) _ Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat said
``peace needs a gun to defend it'' in an interview broadcast on
Spanish television on Wednesday.
	   The head of the Palestinian Authority also called on the
international community to take responsibility for the Mideast
peace process he said was threatened ``in its entirety'' by the
policies of Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu.
	   ``I am not optimistic because the policies of Netanyahu run
against peace'' Arafat said in the interview recorded at his home
in Gaza on Friday.
	   The Palestinian leader also stressed his current lobbying of
Arab leaders in an effort to organize a summit that would serve as
immediate pressure on Israel to accept a U.S. proposal for an
Israeli troop withdrawal from 13.1 percent of the West Bank.
	   Israel has yet to give a definitive response to the U.S. plan
which has already been accepted by the Palestinians.
	   (jt)
