<HEADLINE>
Precede JERUSALEM
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Palestinian killed by Israeli troops near Jewish settlement &QL; 
 &UR; Eds: UPGRADES attribution, Leads throughout with statement from
army spokesman, details from Palestinian police official &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   GAZA CITY, Gaza Strip (AP) _ A Palestinian was shot and killed
Tuesday by Israeli troops who spotted him and several others trying
to enter a Jewish settlement in the Gaza Strip, the army said.
	   Military officials who spoke on condition of anonymity said the
Palestinian was not armed. An Israeli army statement said an
explosive device was found where the suspects were standing near
the Morag settlement.
	   A statement from the Israeli army spokesman said Israeli
soldiers patrolling near the settlement spotted ``a number of
suspicions persons who tried to enter the Morag settlement. Israeli
forces ... opened fire towards the suspects, as a result one
suspect was killed.''
	   The army said the discovery of the explosive devise led them to
believe that an attack on Israeli patrols or civilians living in
the area was planned.
	   Palestinian police Commander Khaled Abu Oleh said the dead
Palestinian had been taken to Nasser hospital in the
Palestinian-controlled Khan Yunis refugee camp about 15 km south of
Morag. Oleh did not reveal the identity of the dead male but said
that a joint Israeli-Palestinian investigation into the incident
was underway.
	   Most of the Gaza Strip is under Palestinian control while Israel
maintains control of the areas around Jewish settlements and Gaza
's borders with Israel and Egypt.
