<HEADLINE>
Pakistan hangs man found guilty of spying
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ISLAMABAD, Pakistan (AP) _ A man Pakistan says was spying for
its hostile neighbor India was hanged Tuesday in eastern Punjab
province, the state-run news agency said.
	   Bilbeer Singh, an Indian national, was arrested in 1989 on
charges of spying and was found guilty in 1991 and sentenced to
death.
	   Singh was charged with stealing documents about Pakistan's
nuclear installations near the federal capital of Islamabad and
with acquiring information on Pakistani army positions in the
disputed state of Kashmir.
	   Last month both countries detonated nuclear devices and declared
themselves nuclear states.
