<HEADLINE>
Palestinian killed by Israeli troops near Jewish settlement
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: CORRECTS in lead to infiltrate sted enter as per army
statement, adds conversion in graf 5 &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   GAZA CITY, Gaza Strip (AP) _ A Palestinian was shot and killed
Tuesday by Israeli troops who spotted him and several others trying
to infiltrate a Jewish settlement in the Gaza Strip, the army said.
	   Military officials who spoke on condition of anonymity said the
Palestinian was not armed. An Israeli army statement said an
explosive device was found where the suspects were standing near
the Morag settlement.
	   A statement from the Israeli army spokesman said Israeli
soldiers patrolling near the settlement spotted ``a number of
suspicions persons who tried to enter the Morag settlement. Israeli
forces ... opened fire towards the suspects, as a result one
suspect was killed.''
	   The army said the discovery of the explosive device led them to
believe that an attack on Israeli patrols or civilians living in
the area was planned.
	   Palestinian police Commander Khaled Abu Oleh said incident took
place around 23:30 (20:30gmt). He said the dead Palestinian had
been taken to Nasser hospital in the Palestinian-controlled Khan
Yunis refugee camp about 15 km (9 miles) south of Morag. Oleh said
a joint Israeli-Palestinian investigation into the incident was
underway.
	   Officials at Nasser hospital later identified the dead man as
Abud Qanan, a 22 year-old from the Khan Yunis.
	   Most of the Gaza Strip is under Palestinian control while Israel
maintains control of the areas around Jewish settlements and Gaza's
borders with Israel and Egypt.
