<HEADLINE>
Fire breaks out in factory in western France
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: Upgrades attribution, adds no injuries. &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   PARIS (AP) _ Fire broke out Tuesday in a factory near the
western French city of Nantes, police said. No one was injured.
	   A hundred firefighters fought to stop the flames from igniting
vats of ammonia. The factory, owned by the Frigecreme company, was
evacuated, and people in the area were advised to stay in their
homes during the efforts.
	   No further details were immediately available.
	   (parf-jn) 	   
