w2184 &Cx1f; wstm-
r f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Japan-SumitomoLife     06-09 0195
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Japan-Sumitomo Life </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Report: Insurer to form Japan's biggest asset management firm
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TOKYO (AP) _ Sumitomo Life Insurance Co. plans to form Japan's
largest asset management company early next year, a newspaper
reported Wednesday.
	   Sumitomo will create a subsidiary out of an affilated company
that will manage some 10 trillion yen (dlrs 71 billion) in assets,
the Asahi newspaper reported.
	   That would be more than twice as large as Japan's biggest
existing asset management company, the paper said.
	   Sumitomo is one of Japan's top insurers.
	   The new company will establish offices in New York, London, Hong
Kong and Singapore and hire about 30 asset management experts from
overseas companies, the Asahi report said.
	   The new company will be launched in January after a revision in
the country's insurance law allowing subsidiaries goes into effect
in December, it said.
	   Banks and other financial institutions are scrambling to form
new alliances with both domestic and overseas companies in line
with major reforms _ known collectively as the ``big bang'' _ aimed
at increasing competition in Japan's financial industry.
 &UR; (kgo)
</TEXT>
