<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Benfica-MetroStars,0233 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Benfica defeats MetroStars 3-1
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   EAST RUTHERFORD, New Jersey (AP) _ Brian Deane scored two early
goals Tuesday to lead Benfica of Portugal to a 3-1 victory over the
New York-New Jersey MetroStars.
	   In the first half, the MetroStars were unable to contain Deane,
who scored seven goals in 14 games in the Portuguese League after
transferring at midseason from Sheffield Wednesday of England.
	   The striker, who left the game for a substitute in the 52nd
minute, scored on a header in the 13th minute and then beat three
defenders to a low cross in the 22nd minute, flicking the ball into
the goal.
	   The MetroStars, who have won four of their last five Major
League Soccer game, scored in the 25th minute on a penalty kick by
Diego Sonora after Benfica defender Paulo Madeira was called for a
handball in the penalty box.
	   Benfica added an insurance goal in the 88th minute when Ulf
Pringle headed in a cross.
	   The Lisbon-based club, a second-place finisher to Oporto in the
1998 Portuguese League, got two acrobatic saves from Belgian
goalkeeper Michel Preud'homme in the second half to preserve the
victory.
	   Benfica, which features players from eight countries, concludes
its brief trip to the United States on Thursday with a game against
the MLS' New England Revolution in Foxboro, Massachusetts.
</TEXT>
