<SLUG> BC-Australia-Lufthansa </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Lufthansa booking center for Melbourne
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MELBOURNE, Australia (AP) _ German airline Lufthansa will
establish its Asia-Pacific reservations call center in Melbourne, a
move which will create 300 jobs.
	   Industry Minister Mark Birrell said Wednesday the center, due to
open in October, will handle calls from Japan, Hong Kong,
Singapore, New Zealand and Australia, as well as night-time calls
from Europe and the United States.
	   He said Melbourne's main attraction had been its skilled,
multi-lingual population, as well as the possibility of setting up
in the central business district.
	   Beating a number of other cities for the center, including Kuala
Lumpur and Macau, was a ``tremendous coup'' for Melbourne and added
impetus to the government's push to attract more international
companies, he said.
	   Lufthansa reservations vice-president William Pattison said
Melbourne would be one of nine call centers around the world as
Lufthansa sought to centralize its operations away from the current
211 call centers.
</TEXT>
